namaz. We should know that Masjid-e-Hannaanah is of the
merilorious Majids of Najaf-e-Ashraf. 

According to a tradition the head of Imam Husain (a.s.) was placed there and it is related that
when Imam Sadiq (a.s.) recited 2 rakats namaz there people asked
which namaz he (a.s.) had prayed. He (a.s.) said, “This is the place of
the head of my forefather Imam Husain (a.s.)”. The head was
placed here on way from Kerbala to Ibne Ziyad at Kufa. According
to narrations the Imam (a.s.) said that we must recite the following
Dua here: 

O Allah, You can see my place, hear my speech, and nothing of my
affairs can ever conceal itself from You. How come a thing that You
have created and made conceal itself from You? I have come to you
seeking the intercession of Your Prophet – the Prophet of Mercy,
and seeking the mediation of Your Prophet’s successor. So, I
beseech You in the name of both of them to grant me firmness, true
guidance, and forgiveness in this world as well as the world to come""",
