      {
        "title": "Aamal of Masjide Kufa",
        "arabic":
            """According to Misbaah-uz-Zaaereen when you enter Kufa, you must recite:
 بِسْمِ اللهِ وَبِاللهِ وَفي سَبيلِ اللهِ وَعَلى مِلَّةِ رَسُولِ اللهِ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَآلِهِ اَللّـهُمَّ اَنْزِلْني مُنْزَلاً مُبارَكاً وَاَنْتَ خَيْرُ الْمُنْزِلينَ

Move towards the Masjid reciting as follows:
اَللهُ اَكْبَرُ وَلا اِلـهَ اِلاّ اللهُ وَالْحَمْدُ للهِ وَسُبْحانَ اللهِ

When you reach the gate of the Masjid, stop there and recite the following:

اَلسَّلامُ عَلى سَيِّدِنا رَسُولِ اللهِ مُحَمَّدِ بْنِ عَبْدِ اللهِ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَآلِهِ الطّاهِرينَ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلى اَميرِ الْمُؤْمِنينَ عَلِيِّ بْنِ أبي طالِب وَرَحْمَةُ اللهِ وَبَرَكاتُهُ، وَعَلى مَجالِسِهِ وَمَشاهِدِهِ وَمَقامِ حِكْمَتِهِ وَآثارِ آبائِهِ آدَمَ وَنُوح وَاِبْراهيمَ وَاِسْماعيلَ وَتِبْيانِ بَيِّناتِهِ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلَى الاِْمامِ الْحَكيمِ الْعَدْلِ الصِّديقِ الاَْكْبَرِ الْفارُوقِ بِالْقِسْطِ الَّذي فَرَّقَ اللهُ بِهِ بَيْنَ الْحَقِّ وَالْباطِلِ وَالْكُفْرِ وَالاْيمانِ وَالشِّرْكِ وَالتَّوْحيدِ، لِيَهْلِكَ مَنْ هَلَكَ عَنْ بَيِّنَة وَيُحْيا مَنْ حَيَّ عَنْ بَيِّنَة، اَشْهَدُ اَنَّكَ اَميرُ الْمُؤْمِنينَ، وَخاصَّةُ نَفْسِ الْمُنْتَجَبينَ، وَزَيْنُ الصِّديقينَ، وَصابِرُ الْمُمْتَحَنينَ، وَاَنَّكَ حَكَمُ اللهِ في اَرْضِهِ، وَقاضي اَمْرِهِ، وَبابُ حِكْمَتِهِ، وَعاقِدُ عَهْدِهِ، وَالنّاطِقُ بِوَعْدِهِ، وَالْحَبْلُ الْمَوْصُولُ بَيْنَهُ وَبَيْنَ عِبادِهِ، وَكَهْفُ النَّجاةِ، وَمِنْهاجُ التُّقي، وَالدَّرَجَةُ الْعُلْيا، وَمُهَيْمِنُ الْقاضِي الاَْعْلى، يا اَميرَ الْمُؤْمِنينَ بِكَ اَتَقَرَّبُ اِلَى اللهِ زُلْفى، اَنْتَ وَلِيِّي وَسَيِّدي وَوَسيلَتي فِي الدُّنْيا وَالاْخِرَةِ

Then enter the Masjid, and it is better to enter through the gate known as Bab-ul-Feel. After entering, recite the following:

اَللهُ اَكْبَرُ اَللهُ اَكْبَرُ اَللهُ اَكْبَرُ هذا مَقامُ الْعائِذِ بِاللهِ وَبِمُحَمَّد حَبيبِ اللهِ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَآلِهِ، وَبِوِلايَةِ اَميرِ الْمُؤْمِنينَ وَالاَْئِمَّةِ الْمَهْدِيّينَ الصّادِقينَ النّاطِقينَ الرّاشِدينَ الَّذينَ اَذْهَبَ اللهُ عَنْهُمُ الرِّجْسَ وَطَهَّرَهُمْ تَطْهيراً، رَضيتُ بِهِمْ اَئِمَّةً وَهُداةً وَمَوالِيَ سَلَّمْتُ لاَِمْرِ اللهِ لا اُشْرِكُ بِهِ شَيْئاً، وَلا اَتَّخِذُ مَعَ اللهِ وَلِيّاً، كَذَبَ الْعادِلُونَ بِاللهِ وَضَلُّوا ضَلالاً بَعيداً، حَسْبِيَ اللهُ وَاَوْلِياءُ اللهِ اَشْهَدُ اَنْ لا اِلـهَ اِلاَّ اللهُ وَحْدَهُ لا شَريكَ لَهُ، وَاَشْهَدُ اَنَّ مُحَمَّداً عَبْدُهُ وَرَسُولُهُ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَآلِهِ وَاَنَّ عَلِيّاً وَالاَْئِمَّةَ الْمَهْدِيّينَ مِنْ ذُرِّيَّتِهِ عَلَيْهِمُ السَّلامُ اَوْلِيائي وَحُجَّةُ اللهِ عَلى خَلْقِهِ""",
        "translation":
            """According to Misbaah-uz-Zaaereen when you enter Kufa, you must recite:

In the name of Allah, by Allah, in the path of Allah and on the path of
the Prophet of Allah, peace be on him and his family. O Allah, make
me go forth with blessings, because You are the best of those who
bring people forth.

Move towards the Masjid reciting as follows: 

Allah is great, there is no god but Allah, praise be to Allah, glory be to Allah.

When you reach the gate of the Masjid, stop there and recite the following: 


Peace be on our master, the Prophet of Allah, Muhammad b.
‘Abdullah, peace be on him and his pine family. Peace be on the
Commander of the Faithful. Ali b. Abi Talib, may the mercy and
blessings of Allah be on him and on where he met with people,
where testimony was given, and where he delivered his decisions.
Peace be on his ancestors Adam, Nuh, Ibrahim and Isma’il and on
the explanations of His proofs. Peace be on the wise Imam, the just,
truthful and the greatest one, the one who judges with justice
through whom Allah distinguishes between truth and falsehood,
and between disbelief and true belief, polytheism and monotheism
so that those who are destroyed are destroyed after clear signs were
delivered to them. Those who are revived are revived due to clear signs to them. I bear witness that you are the Commander of the
Faithful especially for the souls of the chosen ones and an ornament
of the truthful ones and patience for those tried. I bear witness that
you are the command of Allah on His earth, one who implements His
commands; you are the door to His wisdom; undertaker of His
covenant and you speak by His promise. You are the rope that is
connected between Him and His slaves. You are the cave of
salvation and the path of righteousness, the highest level of
uprightness and the greatest judge. O Commander of the Faithful,
through you I seek closeness to Allah. You are my guardian, my
master and my intermediary in this world and in the next. 

Then enter the Masjid, and it is better to enter through the gate known as Bab-ul-Feel. After entering, recite the following:

Allah is great, Allah is great, Allah is great. This is the position of one
who seeks refuge in Allah and by Muhammad, the beloved of Allah
peace be on him and his family, and by the guardianship of the
Commander of the Faithful and the rightly guided, truthful leaders.
They are the ones from whom Allah has removed all filth and
purified them completely. I am satisfied with them as my Imams,
guides and masters. I have submitted to the command of Allah. I do
not associate anyone with Him nor do I take a partner with Allah.
The extremists have lied against Allah, they have gone completely
astray. Allah and His special servants are sufficient for me. I bear
witness that there is no god but Allah, He is one, there is no partner
unto Him. I bear witness that Muhammad is His slave and Prophet,
peace be on him and his family, and that Ali (a.s.) and the rightly
guided Imams (a.s.) from his progeny are the friends of Allah, they
are proofs of Allah on His creatures.""",
