      {
        "title": "The Fourth Pillar",
        "arabic":
            """(It is beside the pillar of Janabe Ibrahim (a.s.), i.e. the fifth Pillar). Recite 4 rakats Namaz here. In the first 2 rakats after Surah Hamd recite Surah Tawheed and in the next 2 rakats, after Surah Hamd recite Surah Qadr. After the Namaz recite the Tasbeeh of Hazrat Fatemah Zahra (s.a.). Then recite the following Dua:
        
(It is beside the pillar of Janabe Ibrahim (a.s.), i.e. the fifth Pillar). Recite 4 rakats Namaz here. In the first 2 rakats after Surah Hamd recite Surah Tawheed and in the next 2 rakats, after Surah Hamd recite Surah Qadr. After the Namaz recite the Tasbeeh of Hazrat Fatemah Zahra (s.a.). Then recite the following Dua:

Then read the following 7 times.
سَلامٌ عَلى نُوح فِى الْعالَمينَ

Then recite:

نَحْنُ عَلى وَصِيَّتِكَ يا وَلِيَّ الْمُؤْمِنينَ الَّتي اَوْصَيْتَ بِها ذُرِّيَّتَكَ مِنَ الْمُرْسَلينَ وَالصِّدّيقينَ، وَنَحْنُ مِنْ شيعَتِكَ وَشيعَةِ نَبِيِّنا مُحَمَّد صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَآلِهِ وَعَلَيْكَ وَعَلى جَميعِ الْمُرْسَلينَ وَالاَْنْبِياءِ وَالصّادِقينَ، وَنَحْنُ عَلى مِلَّةِ اِبْرهيمَ وَدينِ مُحَمَّدّ النَّبِيِّ الاُْمِّيِّ وَالاَْئِمَّةِ الْمَهْدِيّينَ وَوِلايَةِ مَوْلانا عَلِيٍّ اَميرِ الْمُؤْمِنينَ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلَى الْبَشيرِ النَّذيرِ صَلَواتُ اللهِ عَلَيْهِ وَرَحْمَتُهُ وَرِضْوانُهُ وَبَرَكاتُهُ، وَعَلى وَصِيِّهِ وَخَليفَتِهِ الشّاهِدِ للهِ مِنْ بَعْدِهِ عَليٍّ خَلْقِهِ عَلى اَميرِ الْمُؤْمِنينَ الصِّديقِ الاَْكْبَرِ وَالْفارُوقِ الْمُبينِ، الَّذى اَخَذْتَ بَيْعَتَهُ عَلَى الْعالَمينَ، رَضيتُ بِهِمْ اَوْلِياءَ وَمَوالِيَ وَحُكّاماً في نَفْسي وَوُلْدي وَاَهْلي وَمالي وَقِسْمي وَحِلّي وَاِحْرامي وَاِسْلامي وَديني وَدُنْيايَ وَآخِرَتي وَمَحْيايَ وَمَماتي، اَنْتُمُ الاَْئِمَّةُ فِي الْكِتابِ وَفَصْلُ الْمَقامِ وَفَصْلُ الْخِطابِ، وَاَعْيُنُ الْحَيِّ الَّذي لا يَنامُ، وَاَنْتُمْ حُكَماءُ، اللهِ وَبِكُمْ حَكَمَ اللهُ وَبِكُمْ عِرُفَ حَقُّ اللهِ، لا اِلـهَ اِلاَّ اللهُ مُحَمَّدٌ رَسُولُ اللهِ، اَنْتُمْ نُورُ اللهِ مِنْ بَيْنِ اَيْدينا وَمِنْ خَلْفِنا، اَنْتُمْ سُنَّةُ اللهِ الَّتي بِها سَبَقَ الْقَضاءُ، يا اَميرَ الْمُؤْمِنينَ اَنَا لَكُمْ مُسَلِّمٌ تَسْليماً لا اُشْرِكُ بِاللهِ شَيْئاً وَلا اَتَّخِذُ مِنْ دُونِهِ وَلِيّاً، اَلْحَمْدُ للهِ الَّذي هَداني بِكُمْ وَما كُنْتُ لاَِهْتَدِيَ لَوْلا اَنْ هَدانِيَ اللهُ، اَللهُ اَكْبَرُ اَللهُ اَكْبَرُ اَللهُ اَكْبَرُ، الْحَمْدُ للهِ عَلى ما هَدانا""",
        "translation":
            """(It is beside the pillar of Janabe Ibrahim (a.s.), i.e. the fifth Pillar).
Recite 4 rakats Namaz here. In the first 2 rakats after Surah Hamd
recite Surah Tawheed and in the next 2 rakats, after Surah Hamd
recite Surah Qadr. After the Namaz recite the Tasbeeh of Hazrat
Fatemah Zahra (s.a.). Then recite the following Dua: 

Peace be on the upright guided servants of Allah from whom Allah
has removed all impurities and has purified them completely. He
sent them as Prophets and proofs on all His creatures. Peace be on
the Prophets, praise be to Allah the Lord of the Universe that is the
decree of the most powerful, the most knowing. 

Then read the following 7 times.

Peace be on Nuh in the Universe. 

Then recite:

O friend of the believers, we follow your testament that you left to
your progeny amongst the messengers and the truthful ones. We
are your followers and the followers of our Prophet Muhammad,
peace be on him and his family and peace be on you and on all the
Messengers, Prophets and the truthful ones. We are on the path of
Ibrahim and on the path of Muhammad, the ummi Prophet and the
guided Imams and we follow the leadership of our master ‘Ali, the
Commander of the Faithful. Peace be on one who brings good
tidings, the warner. May Allah send His mercy and blessings on him
and his family and on his successor, His representative and His proof
one who will bear witness to Allah after him over His creatures, ‘Ah,
the Commander of the Faithful. He is the greatest, most truthful,
one who clearly distinguishes between truth and falsehood, the one
whose oath of allegiance You have made incumbent over the Universe. I am happy with them as my leaders, masters and judges
for myself, my children, my family, over my wealth, my share and in
what is allowed and not allowed for me, in my religion, my path, in
my world and in my hereafter, in my life and death. You are the
Imams in the book and the final station and word. You are the
watchful eyes that do not sleep and you are the judges of Allah.
Through you, Allah judges and, through you, the truth of Allah is
known. There is no god but Allah, Muhammad is the Prophet of
Allah, peace be on him and his family. You are the light of Allah in
front of and behind us. You are the laws of Allah through which the
decree is made. O Commander of the Faithful, I submit myself to you
completely, I do not associate any partner with Allah neither do I
take any other lord besides Him. Praise be to Allah who has guided
me through you, I would not have been guided had not Allah
guided me. Allah is great, Allah is great, Allah is great. Praise be to
Allah for what He has guided me to.""",
