      {
        "title": "Dakkatul Qazaa and Baitut Tasht",
        "arabic":
            """These two places are near to each other. Dakkatul Qazaa is named thus because Hazrat Ali bin Abi Talib (a.s.) used to sit at this place and give legal judgements. Baitul Tasht is named thus because Hazrat (a.s.) had given a miraculous judgement here. When a young unmarried girl was brought to him with signs of pregnancy. Due to this the brothers of this girl wanted to kill her. The problem was taken to Hazrat Ali (a.s.). He (a.s.) extended his hand and acquired a piece of ice from the mountain of Syria and kept it near a tray, and made the girl sit upon it. 
A ‘leech’ had overgrown in the belly of the girl and it came out and it was learnt that she was not pregnant but she had a ‘leech’ in her stomach. The reason was that, one day the girl was bathing when the ‘leech’ entered her stomach. It continued to suck blood and grow up. This caused people to doubt her character. By this judgement of Hazrat Ali (a.s.) the girl was proved innocent and her life was saved.
This teaches us a lesson that without reaching to the truth we should not accuse anyone on the basis of outward appearance

Aamals of Dakkatul Qazaa

Recite two rakats namaz here and then recite the Tasbeeh of Hazrat Fatemah Zahra (s.a.). After the tasbeeh recite the following dua:

يا مالِكي وَمُمَلِّكي وَمُتَغَمِّدي بِالنِّعَمِ الْجِسامِ مِنْ غَيْرِ اسْتِحْقاق، وَجْهي خاضِعٌ لِما تَعْلُوهُ الاَْقْدامُ لِجَلالِ وَجْهِكَ الْكَريمِ، لا تَجْعَلْ هذِهِ الشِّدَّةَ وَلا هذِهِ الِْمحْنَةَ مُتَّصِلَةً بِاِسْتئصالِ الشَّأفَةِ وَامْنَحْني مِنْ فَضْلِكَ ما لَمْ تَمْنَحْ بِهِ اَحَداً مِنْ غَيْرِ مَسْأَلَة، اَنْتَ الْقَديمُ الاَْوَّلُ الَّذي لَمْ تَزَلْ وَلا تَزالُ، صَلِّ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِ مُحَمَّد وَاغْفِرْ لي وَارْحَمْني وَزَكِّ عَمَلي، وَبارِكْ لي في اَجَلي، وَاجْعَلْني مِنْ عُتَقائِكَ وَطُلَقائِكَ مِنَ النّارِ بِرَحْمَتِكَ يا اَرْحَمَ الرّاحِمينَ

Aamals of Dakkatul Qazaa

Recite two rakats namaz here and then recite the Tasbeeh of Hazrat Fatemah Zahra (s.a.). After the tasbeeh recite the following dua:

يا مالِكي وَمُمَلِّكي وَمُتَغَمِّدي بِالنِّعَمِ الْجِسامِ مِنْ غَيْرِ اسْتِحْقاق، وَجْهي خاضِعٌ لِما تَعْلُوهُ الاَْقْدامُ لِجَلالِ وَجْهِكَ الْكَريمِ، لا تَجْعَلْ هذِهِ الشِّدَّةَ وَلا هذِهِ الِْمحْنَةَ مُتَّصِلَةً بِاِسْتئصالِ الشَّأفَةِ وَامْنَحْني مِنْ فَضْلِكَ ما لَمْ تَمْنَحْ بِهِ اَحَداً مِنْ غَيْرِ مَسْأَلَة، اَنْتَ الْقَديمُ الاَْوَّلُ الَّذي لَمْ تَزَلْ وَلا تَزالُ، صَلِّ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِ مُحَمَّد وَاغْفِرْ لي وَارْحَمْني وَزَكِّ عَمَلي، وَبارِكْ لي في اَجَلي، وَاجْعَلْني مِنْ عُتَقائِكَ وَطُلَقائِكَ مِنَ النّارِ بِرَحْمَتِكَ يا اَرْحَمَ الرّاحِمينَ""",
        "translation":
            """These two places are near to each other. Dakkatul Qazaa is named thus because Hazrat Ali bin Abi Talib (a.s.) used to sit at this place and give legal judgements. Baitul Tasht is named thus because Hazrat (a.s.) had given a miraculous judgement here. When a young unmarried girl was brought to him with signs of pregnancy.Due to this the brothers of this girl wanted to kill her. The problem was taken to Hazrat Ali (a.s.). He (a.s.) extended his hand and acquired a piece of ice from the mountain of Syria and kept it near a tray, and made the girl sit upon it. 

A ‘leech’ had overgrown in the belly of the girl and it came out and it was learnt that she was not pregnant but she had a ‘leech’ in her stomach. The reason was that, one day the girl was bathing when the ‘leech’ entered her stomach. It continued to suck blood and grow up. This caused people to doubt her character. By this judgement of Hazrat Ali (a.s.) the girl was proved innocent and her life was saved

This teaches us a lesson that without reaching to the truth we should not accuse anyone on the basis of outward appearance. 

Aamals of Dakkatul Qazaa as follows:

Recite two rakats namaz here and then recite the Tasbeeh of
Hazrat Fatemah Zahra (s.a.). After the tasbeeh recite the following dua:

O Allah, I have accumulated my [praises of] unity for You only and
my knowledge of You only. My sincerity is for You and I profess to
Your Lordship. I have kept my allegiance for the one whose
knowledge You have blessed me with amongst Your creation,
Muhammad and his family, peace be on them, for the day of anxiety
when I hasten to You. I have sought asylum in You and in them, O my master on this day and in this position of mine, and I ask You to
increase Your blessings and remove Your retributions that I fear.
Grant me blessings in the sustenance that You bestow. I ask that
You strengthen my heart in all difficulties and sins, in my religion, in
my world and in my hereafter, O most merciful of the merciful ones

Aamaal of Baitut Tasht as follows:

Recite two rakats namaz and after Tasbeeh of Hazrat Fatemah Zahra (s.a.) recite the following dua:

O Allah, You are the peace and from You is peace and peace returns
to You and Your abode is the abode of peace. Enliven us, O our Lord,
with peace from You. O Allah, I have offered these prayers seeking
Your mercy, pleasure and forgiveness out of respect of Your
mosque. O Allah, send Your blessings on Muhammad and on the
family of Muhammad and raise the prayers to the station of
‘illiyyeen’ in heaven and accept these prayers from me, O most merciful of the merciful ones.""",
