      {
        "title": "The Seventh Pillar",
        "arabic": """Aamaal of Seventh Pillar

This is a very important pillar. Hazrat Ali (a.s.) used to pray here. It is the place where Allah had accepted the repentance of Hazrat Adam (a.s.). 

First face the Qibla and then recite the following Dua:

بِسْمِ اللهِ وَبِاللهِ وَعَلى مِلَّةِ رَسُولِ اللهِ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَآلِهِ، وَلا اِلـهَ اِلاَّ اللهُ، مُحَمَّدٌ رَسُولُ اللهِ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلى اَبينا آدَمَ وَاُمِّنا حَوّاءَ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلى هابيلَ الْمَقْتُول ظُلْماً وَعُدْواناً عَلى مَواهِبِ اللهِ وَرِضْوانِهِ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلى شَيْث صَفْوَةِ اللهِ الُْمخْتارِ الاَْمينِ وَعَلَى الصَّفْوَةِ الصّادِقينَ مِنْ ذُرِّيَّتِهِ الطَّيِّبينَ اَوَّلِهِمْ وَآخَرِهِمْ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلى اِبْرهيمَ وَاِسْماعيلَ وَاِسْحاقَ وَيَعْقُوبَ وَعَلى ذُرِّيَّتِهِمُ الُْمخْتارينَ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلى مُوسى كَليمِ اللهِ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلى عيسى رُ��حِ اللهِ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلى مُحَمَّدِ بْنِ عَبْدِ اللهِ خاتَمِ النَّبِيّينَ اَلسَّلامُ عَلى اَميرِ الْمُؤْمِنينَ وَذُرِّيَّتِهِ الطَّيّبينَ وَرَحْمَةُ اللهِ وَبَرَكاتُهُ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكُمْ فِي الاَْوَّلينَ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكُمْ فِي الاْخِرينَ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلى فاطِمَةَ الزَّهْراءِ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلَى الاَْئِمَّةِ الْهادينَ شُهَداءِ اللهِ عَلى خَلْقِهِ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلَى الرَّقيبِ الشّاهِدِ عَلَى الاُْمَمِ للهِ رَبِّ الْعالَمينَ

After this recite 4 rakats prayer in units of 2 rakats each. In the first rakat after surah Hamd recite surah Qadr, in the second rakat after surah Hamd recite surah Tawheed, third and fourth rakats should also be prayed in the same way. After Tasbeeh of Hazrat Fatemah Zahra (s.a.) recite the following dua.

اَللّـهُمَّ اِنْ كُنْتُ قَدْ عَصَيْتُكَ فَاِنّي قَدْ اَطَعْتُكَ فِي الاْيمانِ مِنّي بِكَ مَنّاً مِنْكَ عَلَيَّ لا مَنّاً مِنّي عَلَيْكَ، وَاَطَعْتُكَ في اَحَبِّ الاَْشْياءِ لَكَ لَمْ اَتَّخِذ لَكَ وَلَداً وَلَمْ اَدْعُ لَكَ شَريكاً، وَقَدْ عَصَيْتُكَ في اَشْياء كَثيرَة عَلى غَيْرِ وَجْهِ الْمُكابَرَةِ لَكَ، وَلاَ الْخُرُوجِ عَنْ عُبُودِيَّتِكَ، وَلاَ الْجُحُودِ لِرُبُوبِيَّتِكَ، وَلكِنِ اتَّبَعْتُ هَوايَ وَاَزَلَّنِي الشَّيْطانُ بَعْدَ الْحُجَّةِ عَلَيَّ وَالْبَيانِ

فَاِنْ تُعَذِّبْني فَبِذُنُوبي غَيْرَ ظالِم لي، وَاِنْ تَعْفُ عَنّي وَتَرْحَمْني فَبِجُودِكَ وَكَرَمِكَ يا كَريمُ، اَللّـهُمَّ اِنَّ ذُنُوبي لَمْ يَبْقَ لَها اِلاّ رَجاءُ عَفْوِكَ، وَقَدْ قَدَّمْت آلَةَ الْحِرْمانِ، فَاَنَا اَسْاَلُكَ اللّهُمَّ ما لا اَسْتَوْجِبُهُ، وَاَطْلُبُ مِنْكَ ما لا اَسْتِحَقُّهُ، اَللّـهُمَّ اِنْ تُعَذِّبْني فَبِذُنُوبي وَلَمْ تَظْلِمْني شَيْئاً ، وَاِنْ تَغْفِرْ لي فَخَيْرُ راحِم اَنْتَ يا سَيِّدي، اَللّـهُمَّ اَنْتَ اَنْتَ وَأَنَا أَنَا، اَنْتَ الْعَوّادُ بِالْمَغْفِرَةِ وَاَنَا الْعَوّادُ بِالذُّنُوبِ، وَاَنْتَ الْمُتَفَضِّلُ بِالْحِلْمِ وَاَنَا الْعَوّادُ بِالْجَهْلِ، اَللّـهُمَّ فَاِنّي اَسْاَلُكَ يا كَنْزَ الضُّعَفاءِ، يا عَظيمَ الرَّجاءِ، يا مُنْقِذَ الْغَرْقى، يا مُنْجِيَ الْهَلَكى، يا مُميتَ الاَْحْياءِ، يا مُحْيِيَ الْمَوْتى، اَنْتَ اللهُ لا اِلـهَ اِلاّ اَنْتَ، اَنْتَ الَّذي سَجَدَ لَكَ شُعاعُ الشَّمْسِ وَدَوِيُّ الْماءِ وَحَفيفُ الشَّجَرِ وَنُورُ الْقَمَرِ وَظُلْمَةُ اللَّيْلِ وَضَوْءُ النَّهارِ وَخَفَقانُ الطَّيْرِ، فَأَسْأَلُكَ اللّهُمَّ يا عَظيمُ بِحَقِّكَ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِهِ الصّادِقينَ، وَبِحَقِّ مُحَمَّد وَآلِهِ الصّادِقينَ عَلَيْكَ، وَبِحَقِّكَ عَلى عَلِيٍّ وَبِحَقِّ عَلِيٍّ عَلَيْكَ، وَبِحَقِّكَ عَلى فاطِمَةَ وَبِحَقِّ فاطِمَةَ عَلَيْكَ، وَبِحَقِّكَ عَلَى الْحَسَنِ وَبِحَقِّ الْحَسَنِ عَلَيْكَ، وَبِحَقِّكَ عَلَى الْحُسَيْنِ وَبِحَقِّ الْحُسَيْنِ، عَلَيْكَ فَاِنَّ حُقُوقَهُمْ عَلَيْكَ مِنْ اَفْضَلِ اِنْعامِكَ عليهم، وَبِالشَّأنِ الَّذي لَكَ عِنْدَهُمْ، وَبِالشَّأنِ الَّذي لَهُمْ عِنْدَكَ، صَلِّ عَلَيْهِمْ يا رَبِّ صَلاةً دائِمَةً مُنْتَهى رِضاكَ، وَاغْفِرْ لي بِهِمُ الذُّنُوبَ الَّتي بَيْني وَبَيْنَكَ، وَاَرْضِ عَنّي خَلْقَكَ، وَاَتْمِمْ عَلَيَّ نِعْمَتَكَ كَما اَتْمَمْتَها عَلى آبائي مِنْ قَبْلُ، وَلا تَجْعَلْ لاَِحَد مِنَ الَْمخْلُوقينَ عَلي فيهَا امْتِناناً، وَامْنُنْ عَلَيَّ كَما مَنَنْتَ عَلى آبائي مِنْ قَبْلُ يا كهيعص، اَللّـهُمَّ كَما صَلَّيْتَ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِهِ فَاسْتَجِبْ لي دُعآئي فيـما سَأَلْتُ يا كَريمُ يا كَريمُ يا كَريمُ

Go into the Sajdah and say:

يا مَنْ يَقْدِرُ عَلى حَوائِجِ السّائِلينَ، وَيَعْلَمُ ما في ضَميرِ الصّامِتينَ، يا مَنْ لا يَحْتاجُ اِلَى التَّفْسيرِ، يا مَنْ يَعْلَمُ خائِنَةَ الاَْعْيُنِ وَما تُخْفِي الصُّدُورُ، يا مَنْ اَنْزَلَ الْعَذابَ عَلى قَوْمِ يُونُسَ وَهُوَ يُريدُ اَنْ يُعَذِّبَهُمْ فَدَعَوْهُ وَتَضَرَّعُوا اِلَيْهِ فَكَشَفَ عَنْهُمُ الْعَذابَ وَمَتَّعَهُمْ اِلى حين، قَدْ تَرى مَكاني، وَتَسْمَعُ دُعائي، وَتَعْلَمُ سِرّي وَعَلانِيَتي وَحالي، صَلِّ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِ مُحَمَّد وَاكْفِني ما اَهَمَّني مِنْ اَمْرِ ديني وَدُنْيايَ وَآخِرَتي 

Then repeat 70 times
 يا سَيِّدي

Sit up after the Sajdah and say:

 يا رَبِّ اَسْاَلُكَ بَرَكةَ هذَا الْمَوْضِعِ وَبَرَكَةَ اَهْلِهِ،وَاَسْاَلُكَ اَنْ تَرْزُقَني مِنْ رِزْقِكَ رِزْقاً حَلالاً طَيِّباً تَسُوقُهُ اِلَيَّ بِحَوْلِكَ وَقُوَّتِكَ، وَاَنَا خائِضٌ في عافِيَة، يا اَرْحَمَ الرّاحِمينَ""",
        "translation": """Aamaal of Seventh Pillar as follows:

This is a very important pillar. Hazrat Ali (a.s.) used to pray here. It is the place where Allah had accepted the repentance of Hazrat
Adam (a.s.).

First face the Qibla and then recite the following Dua:

In the name of Allah, by Allah and on the path of the Prophet of
Allah, peace be on him and his family. There is no god but Allah,
Muhammad is the Prophet of Allah. Peace be on our father Adam
and on our mother Hawaa and on Habil, the one who was killed
unjustly due to enmity. Peace be on the gifts of Allah and His pleasures. Peace be on Sheesh, the chosen one of Allah and the
trustworthy one and on the truthful, pure ones from his pure
progeny, the first and last ones. Peace be on Ibrahim, Isma’il, Ishaq,
Ya’qub and on their progeny, the chosen ones. Peace be on Musa,
the one who spoke to Allah. Peace be on ‘Isa, the spirit of Allah.
Peace be on Muhammad b. ‘Abd Allah, the seal of the Prophets.
Peace be on the Commander of the Faithful and his pure progeny,
may the mercy and blessings of Allah be on them. Peace be on you
at the beginning, peace be on you at the end. Peace be on Fatima
Az-Zahra, peace be on the Imams, the guides bearing witness to
Allah on His creatures. Peace be on the watchers, ones who bear
witness on the nations for Allah, the Lord of the Universe. 

After this recite 4 rakats prayer in units of 2 rakats each. In the first
rakat after surah Hamd recite surah Qadr, in the second rakat after
surah Hamd recite surah Tawheed, third and fourth rakats should
also be prayed in the same way. After Tasbeeh of Hazrat Fatemah
Zahra (s.a.) recite the following dua. 

O my Allah, if I have disobeyed You then I have obeyed by my
complete faith in You, bestow Your favors on me for I cannot do
favors to You. I have obeyed You in the things You love most. I do
not attribute a son to You nor do I associate a partner with You. I
have disobeyed You in many things without being arrogant or
denying worship to You nor denying Your Lordship. But I followed
my desires and Shaitan misguided me even though I had clear
proofs and signs. If You punish me then it will be due to my sins. You
will not be unjust to me. If You forgive me and have mercy on me
then it will be due to Your generosity and nobility, O noble one. O
my Allah, there is no recourse in my sins except hope in Your forgiveness. 

I have come with the tools of depravity so I ask You, O
Allah, what I do not deserve and I seek from You what I am not
worthy of. O Allah, if You punish me it will be due to my sins and
You will not have wronged me at all but if You forgive me it will be
because You are the most merciful, O my master. O Allah, You are
what You are and I am what I am. You are the one who repeatedly
forgives, I am one who repeatedly sins. You are the one who
bestows forbearance whereas I return to ignorance. O Allah, I ask
You, O One who is the treasury of the weak ones, O mighty in hopes.
O One who saves those who drown, O One who saves those who are
destroyed, O One who takes away life and O One who gives life to
those who are dead. You are Allah there is no god but You. You are
the one to whom the rays of the sun bow down, tire reverberation of the water, the rustling of the trees and the light of tire moon, the
darkness of the night, the brightness of the day and tire fluttering of the birds submit to You. So I ask You. 

O Allah, O most great by Your right on Muhammad (s.a.w.a.) and his truthful family and by the
right of Muhammad (s.a.w.a.) and his family on You. I ask You by
Your right on Ali (a.s.) and by the right of Ali (a.s.) on You and I ask
You by Your right on Fatima (s.a.) and by the right of Fatima (s.a.) on
You. I ask You by Your right on al-Hasan (a.s.) and by the right of alHasan (a.s.) on You. I ask You by Your right on al-Husain (a.s.) and
the right of al-Husain (a.s.) on You. Indeed, their rights are due to
Your great blessings on them and due to the status they enjoy in
front of You. Send Your blessings on them, O Lord, with eternal
blessings and Your utmost pleasure. So, because of them, forgive
the sins that come between You and me. Make Your creatures
happy with me and perfect Your blessings on me just as You did to
my ancestors before. Do not make any of Your creatures favor me.
Bestow Your favors on me just as You bestowed favors on my
ancestors before. O Qaf, Ha, Ya, Ain, Sad. O Allah, as You send
blessings on Muhammad (s.a.w.a.) and his family, so answer my
prayers concerning what I have asked of You, O Noble One. O Noble
One, O Noble One. O Noble One. 

Go into the Sajdah and say:

O one who has power over the needs of those who ask and knows
what is the minds of those who are quiet, O one who does not
require explanation, O one who recognizes the deception of the
eyes and what the hearts conceal. O one who sent down punishment on the people of Yunus when He wanted to punish
them. They implored and beseeched Him and He removed the punishment and let them live. O Allah, You have seen my position
and heard my supplications and know my private and my public life
and my circumstances. Send Your blessings on Muhammad and the family of Muhammad and remove what troubles me in the affairs of my religion, my world and in my hereafter.

Then repeat 70 times: O my master.

Sit up after the Sajdah and say: O Lord, I ask You for the blessings of this place and the blessings of
its people. I ask You to bestow on me sustenance that is halaal and
pure, by Your power and might, I ask for good health, O most
merciful of the merciful ones.""",
