        "title": "Ziyarat of Janaab Haani Ibne Urwah (r.a.) ",
        "arabic":
            """After the Ziyarat of Janab Muslim Ibne Aqeel (a.s.), one must go for the Ziyarat of Janaab Haani Ibne Urwah (r.a.). First recite the salutation upon the Holy Prophet (s.a.w.a.) and then say:

سَلامُ اللهِ الْعَظيمِ وَصَلَواتُهُ عَلَيْكَ يا هانِيَ بْنَ عُرْوَةَ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكَ اَيُّهَا الْعَبْدُ الصّالِحُ النّاصِحُ للهِ وَلِرَسُولِهِ وَلاَِميرِ الْمُؤْمِنينَ وَالْحَسَنِ وَالْحُسَيْنِ عَلَيْهِمُ السَّلامُ، اَشْهَدُ اَنَّكَ قُتِلْتَ مَظْلُوماً، فَلَعَنَ اللهُ مَنْ قَتَلَكَ وَاسْتَحَلَّ دَمَكَ، وَحَشى قُبُورَهُمْ ناراً، اَشْهَدُ اَنَّكَ لَقِيْتَ اللهَ وَهُوَ راض عَنْكَ بِما فَعَلْتَ وَنَصَحْتَ، وَاَشْهَدُ اَنَّكَ قَدْ بَلَغْتَ دَرَجَةَ الشُّهَداءِ وَجَعَلَ رُوحَكَ مَعَ اَرْواحِ السُّعَداءِ بِما نَصَحْتَ للهِ وَلِرَسُولِهِ مُجْتَهِداً، وَبَذَلْتَ نَفْسَكَ في ذاتِ اللهِ وَمَرْضاتِهِ، فَرَحِمَكَ اللهُ وَرَضِيَ عَنْكَ وَحَشَرَكَ مَعَ مُحَمَّد وَآلِهِ الطّاهِرينَ، وَجَمَعَنا وَاِيّاكُمْ مَعَهُمْ في دارِ النَّعيمِ، وَسَلامٌ عَلَيْكَ وَرَحْمَةُ اللهِ وَبَرَكاتُهُ""",
        "translation":
            """After the Ziyarat of Janab Muslim Ibne Aqeel (a.s.), one must go for
the Ziyarat of Janaab Haani Ibne Urwah (r.a.). First recite the
salutation upon the Holy Prophet (s.a.w.a.) and then say:

Peace be on the Prophet of Allah, greetings on him and his family.
Peace and greetings of Allah, the most mighty, be on you, O Hani b.
‘Urwa. Peace be on you, O upright servant, one who gave good
advice for the sake of Allah, His Prophet, the Commander of the
Faithful and for al- Hasan and al-Husain (a.s.). I bear witness that
you were oppressed when you were killed. May Allah curse those
who killed you and deemed it correct to spill your blood. May Allah
put fire to their graves. I bear witness that you met Allah while He
was pleased with you for what you did and achieved. And I bear
witness that you attained the status of martyrs and your soul has
been kept with the souls of the prosperous ones due to your
achievement by striving for the sake of Allah and His Prophet. You
gave yourself for Allah seeking His pleasure. May Allah have mercy
on you. may He be pleased with you, may He gather you with
Muhammad and his pure family and may He gather you and us with
them in the blessed abode. Peace be on you. may the mercy and blessings of Allah be on you.

After this perform 2 rakats Namaz and gift the reward thereof to the soul of Janaab Haani Ibne Urwah (r.a.). After that ask whatever
dua you like. Recite his farewell also in the similar manner, as mentioned in the farewell of Hazrat Muslim (a.s.).""",
