    'bodies': [
      {
        "title": "Aamal of Masjid Sahla",
        "arabic":
            """After the Masjid of Kufa, the most significant and honorable is the Sahla Masjid. This Masjid had been the residence of Janab-e-Idrees (a.s.) and Janab-e-Ibraahim (a.s.). Janab-e-Khizr (a.s.) used to frequent this place and according to the tradition of Imam Jafar Sadiq (a.s.) after the reappearance, it would be the residence of Hazrat Vali-ul-Asr (a.t.f.s.). He would stay therein with his family. All the prophets have recited namaz in this Masjid. To stay in this Masjid is like staying in the tent of the Holy Prophet (s.a.w.a.) with him. This is the place where Allah desires that morning and evening His name is exalted. The prime time for this Masjid is Wednesday eve.

In this mosque it is recommended to pray 2 rak’ats prayer between Maghrib and Isha. As Imam Sadiq (a.s.) has said: If any sorrowful person will pray this namaz, Allah will ward off his sorrow.

(1) In some books of ziyarat it is mentioned that if you intend to enter the mosque, stand at the gate of the mosque and recite the following Dua:

بِسْمِ اللهِ وَبِاللهِ وَمِنَ اللهِ وَاِلَى اللهِ وَما شاءَ اللهُ وَخَيْرُ الاَْسْماءِ للهِ، وَتَوَكَّلْتُ عَلَى اللهِ وَلا حَوْلَ و لا قُوَّةَ اِلاّ بِاللهِ الْعَلِيِّ الْعَظيمِ، اَللّـهُمَّ اجْعَلْني مِنْ عُمّارِ مَساجِدِكَ وَبُيُوتِكَ، اَللّـهُمَّ اِنّي اَتَوَجَّهُ اِلَيْكَ بِمُحَمَّد وَآلِ مُحَمَّد وَاُقَدِّمُهُمْ بَيْنَ يَدَيْ حَوائِجي، فَاجْعَلْنِي اَللّـهُمَّ بِهِمْ عِنْدَكَ وَجيهاً فِي الدُّنْيا وَالاْخِرةِ وَمِنَ الْمُقَرَّبينَ، اَللّـهُمَّ اجْعَلْ صَلاتي بِهِمْ مَقْبُولَهً، وَذَنْبي بِهِمْ مَغْفُوراً، وَرِزْقي بِهِمْ مَبْسُوطاً، وَدُعائي بِهِمْ مُسْتَجاباً، وَحَوائِجي بِهِمْ مَقْضِيَّةً، وَانْظُرْ اِلَيَّ بِوَجْهِكَ الْكَريمِ نَظَرْةً رَحيمَةً اَسْتَوْجِبُ بِها الْكَرامَةَ عِنْدَكَ، ثُمَّ لا تَصْرِفْهُ عَنّي اَبَداً بِرَحْمَتِكَ يا اَرْحَمَ الرّاحِمينَ، يا مُقَلِّبَ الْقُلُوبِ وَالاَْبْصارِ ثَبِّتْ قَلْبي عَلى دينِكَ وَدينِ نَبِيِّكَ وَوَلِيِّكَ، وَلا تُزِغْ قَلْبي بَعْدَ اِذْ هَدَيْتَني، وَهَبْ لي مِنْ لَدُنْكَ رَحْمَةً اِنَّكَ اَنْتَ الْوَهّابُ، اَللّـهُمَّ اِلَيْكَ تَوَجَّهْتُ وَمَرْضاتَكَ طَلَبْتُ وَثَوابَكَ ابْتَغَيْتُ، وَبِكَ آمَنْتُ وَعَلَيْكَ تَوَكَّلْتُ، اَللّـهُمَّ فَاَقْبِلْ بِوَجْهِكَ ِالَيِّ، وَاَقْبِلْ بِوَجْهي اِلَيْكَ

Then recite Ayatul Kursi, surah Falaq, surah Naas, then recite Tasbihaat-e-Arba seven times as follows:

 سُبْحانَ اللهِ وَالْحَمْدُ للهِ وَلا اِلـهَ اِلاّ اللهُ و اللهُ اَكْبَرُ

And after that recite the following Dua.

اَللّـهُمَّ لَكَ الْحَمْدُ عَلَى ما هَدَيْتَني، وَلَكَ الْحَمْدُ عَلى ما فَضَّلْتَني، وَلَكَ الْحَمْدُ عَلى ما شَرَّفْتَني، وَلَكَ الْحَمْدُ عَلى كُلِّ بَلاء حَسَن ابْتَلَيْتَني، اَللّـهُمَّ تَقَبَّلْ صَلاتي وَدُعائي، وَطَهِّرْ قَلْبي، وَاشْرَحْ لي صَدْري، وَتُبْ عَلَيَّ اِنَّكَ اَنْتَ التَّوّابُ الرَّحيمُ

(2) After praying the Maghrib Namaz and its Naafelah, recite 2 rakat namaz for the honoring of the Masjid. After that raise your hands and recite the following Dua:

اَنْتَ اللهُ لا اِلـهَ اِلاّ اَنْتَ مُبْدِئُ الْخَلْقِ وَمُعيدُهُمْ، وَاَنْتَ اللهُ لا اِلـهَ اِلاّ اَنْتَ خالِقُ الْخَلْقِ وَرازِقُهُمْ، وَاَنْتَ اللهُ لا اِلـهَ اِلاّ اَنْتَ الْقابِضُ الْباسِطُ، وَاَنْتَ اللهُ لا اِلـهَ اِلاّ اَنْتَ مُدَبِّرُ الاُْمُورِ وَباعِثُ مَنْ فِي الْقُبُورِ، اَنْتَ وارِثُ الاَْرْضِ وَمَنْ عَلَيْها، اَسْاَلُكَ بِاسْمِكَ الَمخْزُنِ الْمَكْنُونِ الْحَيِّ الْقَيُّومِ وَاَنْتَ اللهُ لا اِلـهَ اِلاّ اَنْتَ عالِمُ الِسِّر وَاَخْفى، اَسْاَلُكَ بِاسْمِكَ الَّذي اِذا دُعيتَ بِهِ اَجَبْتَ، وَاِذا ِسُئِلْتَ بِهِ اَعْطَيْتَ، وَاَسْاَلُكَ بِحَقِّكَ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَاَهْلِ بَيْتِهِ وَبِحَقِّهِمُ الَّذي اَوْجَبْتَهُ عَلى نَفْسِكَ اَنْ تُصَلِّىَ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِ مُحَمَّد، وَاَنْ تَقْضِيَ لي حاجَتي السّاعَةَ السّاعَةَ، يا سامِعَ الدُّعاءِ، يا سَيِّداهُ يا مَوْلاهُ يا غِياثاهُ، اَسْاَلُكَ بِكُلِّ اسْم سَمَّيْتَ بِهِ نَفْسَكَ اَوْ اسْتَأثَرْتَ بِهِ في عِلْمِ الْغَيْبِ عِنْدَكَ اَنْ تُصَلِّيَ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِ مُحَمَّد، وَاَنْ تُعَجِّلَ فَرَجَنا السّاعَةَ، يا مُقَلِّبَ الْقُلُوبِ وَالاَْبْصارِ، يا سَميعَ الدُّعاءِ

(3) Pray two rakat namaz at the place of Ibrahim (a.s.). After the namaz recite the Tasbeeh of Fatemah Zahra (s.a.) and after this recite the following Dua.

 اَللّـهُمَّ بِحَقِّ هذِهِ الْبُقْعَةِ الشَّريفَةِ، وَبِحَقِّ مِنْ تَعَبَّدَ لَكَ فيها، قَدْ عَلِمْتَ حَوائِجي، فَصَلِّ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِ مُحَمَّد وَاقْضِها، وَقَدْ اَحْصَيْتَ ذُنُوبي فَصَلِّ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِ مُحَمَّد وَاغْفِرْها، اَللّـهُمَّ اَحْيِني ما كاَنَتِ الْحَياةُ خَيْراً لي، وَاَمِتْني اِذا كانَتِ الْوَفاةُ خَيْراً لي عَلى مُوالاةِ اَوْلِيائِكَ وَمُعاداةِ اَعْدائِكَ، وَافْعَلْ بي ما اَنْتَ اَهْلُهُ يا اَرْحَمَ الرّاحِمينَ

(4) Recite 2 rakats namaz at the corner which is to the west and towards the Qibla and after that raise up the hands and recite the following Dua:

 اَللّـهُمَّ اِنّي صَلَّيْتُ هذِهِ الصَّلاةَ ابْتِغاءَ مَرْضاتِكَ، وَطَلَبَ نائِلِكَ، وَرَجاءَ رِفْدِكَ وَجَوائِزِكَ، فَصَلِّ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِ مُحَمَّد وَتَقَبَّلْها مِنّي بِاَحْسَنِ قَبُول، وَبَلِّغْني بِرَحْمَتِكَ الْمَأْمُولَ، وَافْعَلْ بي ما اَنْتَ اَهْلُهُ يا اَرْحَمَ الرّاحِمينَ

Go into the Sajdah and place each cheek on the ground in turn and supplicate Allah.

(5) Recite 2 rakat namaz in the eastern corner. After the namaz raise the hands and recite this dua:

 اَللّـهُمَّ اِنْ كانَتْ الذُّنُوبُ وَالْخَطايا قَدْ اَخْلَقَتْ وَجْهي عِنْدَكَ فَلَمْ تَرْفَعْ لي اِلَيْكَ صَوْتاً وَلَمْ تَسْتَجِبْ لي دَعْوَةً فَاِنّي اَسْاَلُكَ بِكَ يا اللهُ فاَنَّهُ لَيْسَ مِثْلَكَ اَحَدٌ، وَاَتَوَسِّلُ اِلَيْكَ بِمُحَمَّد وَآلِهِ وَاَسْاَلُكَ اَنْ تُصَلِّيَ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِ مُحَمَّد وَاَنْ تُقْبِلَ اِلَيَّ بِوَجْهِكَ الْكَريمِ وَتُقْبِلَ بِوَجْهي اِلَيْكَ وَلا تُخَيِّبْني حَيْنَ اَدْعُوكَ، وَلا تَحْرِمْني حَيْنَ اَرْجُوكَ يا اَرْحَمَ الرّاحِمينَ

(6) After this recite 2 rakats namaz in the other corner in the west side and after the namaz recite the following dua:

 اَللّـهُمَّ اِنّي اَسْاَلُكَ بِاِسْمِكَ يا اللهُ اَنْ تُصَلِّيَ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِ مُحَمَّد، وَاَنْ تَجْعَلَ خَيْرَ عُمْري آخِرَهُ، وَخَيْرَ اَعْمالي خَواتِيمَها وَخَيْرَ اَيّامي يَوْمَ اَلْقاكَ فيهِ اِنَّكَ عَلى كُلِّ شَيْء قَديرٌ، اَللّـهُمَّ تَقَبَّلْ دُعائي وَاسْمَعْ نَجْوايَ يا عَلِيُّ يا عَظيمُ يا قادِرُ يا قاهِرُ يا حَيّاً لا يَمُوتُ، صَلِّ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِ مُحَمَّد وَاغْفِرْ لِيَ الذُّنُوبَ الَّتي بَيْني وَبَيْنَكَ، وَلا تَفْضَحْني عَلى رُؤوسِ الاَْشْهادِ، وَاحْرُسْني بِعينِكَ الَّتي لا تَنامُ وَارْحَمَني بِقُدْرَتِكَ عَلَيَّ يا اَرْحَمَ الرّاحِمينَ، وَصَلَّىَ اللهُ عَلى سَيِّدِنا مُحَمَّد وَآلِهِ الطّاهِرينَ يا رَبَّ الْعالَمينَ

(7) Then recite 2 rakats namaz in the center of the masjid and then recite the following Dua:

 يا مَنْ هُوَ اَقْرَبُ اِلَيَّ مِنْ حَبْلِ الْوَريدِ، يا فَعّالاً لِما يُريدُ، يا مَنْ يَحُولُ بَيْنَ الْمَرْءِ وَقَلْبِهِ صَلِّ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِهِ، وَحُلْ بَيْنَنا وَبَيْنَ مَنْ يُؤْذينا بِحَوْلِكَ وَقُوَّتِكَ يا كافي مِنْ كُلِّ شَيْء وَلا يَكْفي مِنْهُ شَيْءٌ، اِكْفِنا الْمُهِمَّ مِنْ اَمْرِ الدُّنْيا وَالاْخِرَةِ يا اَرْحَمَ الرّاحِمينَ""",
        "translation":
            """After the Masjid of Kufa, the most significant and honorable is the
Sahla Masjid. This Masjid had been the residence of Janab-e-Idrees
(a.s.) and Janab-e-Ibraahim (a.s.). Janab-e-Khizr (a.s.) used to
frequent this place and according to the tradition of Imam Jafar
Sadiq (a.s.) after the reappearance, it would be the residence of
Hazrat Vali-ul-Asr (a.t.f.s.). He would stay therein with his family. All
the prophets have recited namaz in this Masjid. To stay in this
Masjid is like staying in the tent of the Holy Prophet (s.a.w.a.) with
him. This is the place where Allah desires that morning and
evening His name is exalted. The prime time for this Masjid is
Wednesday eve

In this mosque it is recommended to pray 2 rak’ats prayer between Maghrib and Isha. As Imam Sadiq (a.s.) has said:

If any sorrowful person will pray this namaz, Allah will ward off his sorrow. 

(1)In some books of ziyarat it is mentioned that if you intend
to enter the mosque, stand at the gate of the mosque and recite the following Dua:

In the name of Allah, by Allah, from Allah and to Allah and whatever
Allah wills, all the best names are for Allah. I depend on Allah, there
is no power nor might except with Allah, the most High, most Great.
O Allah, make me amongst those who build Your mosques and
houses. O Allah, I have turned to You by Muhammad and his family
and through them, I present my desires. So make me O Allah, due to
them, a notable person in Your eyes in this and the next world.
Make me amongst those close to You. O Allah, due to them, accept
my prayers and supplications. Forgive my sins because of them.
Make my sustenance vast due to them. Because of them, accept my
deeds and look kindly on me O most notable one so that I deserve
Your honor. Then never turn away from me by Your mercy, O most merciful one. O one who over-turns the hearts and sights,
strengthen my heart on Your path and that of Your Prophet and
friends. Do not turn my heart away [from You] having guided me
and bestow mercy on me from You, for You are most giving; O Allah,
I turn to You and I seek Your pleasure and reward. I believe in You, I
depend on You. O Allah, turn to me and make me turn towards You.

Then recite Ayatul Kursi, surah Falaq, surah Naas, then recite

Tasbihaat-e-Arba seven times as follows: 

Glory be to Allah and all Praise is for Allah and there is no god except Allah and Allah is greatest.

And after that recite the following Dua. 

O Allah, praise be to You due to Your guidance and that You
elevated me. Praise be to You due to Your honoring me, praise be to
You due to every good trial which You have tried me by. O Allah,
accept my prayers and supplications; purify my heart and expand
my chest and turn towards me for You are indeed most forgiving and merciful

(2)After praying the Maghrib Namaz and its Naafelah, recite 2 rakat namaz for the honoring of the Masjid. After that raise your hands and recite the following Dua:

You are Allah, there is no god but You; the originator of creation
and one who returns them, there is no god but You. The Creator of
all things and their sustainer; there is no god but You O one who
takes and gives You are Allah, there is no god but You who reckons
affairs and raises those in graves. You cause to inherit those on
earth. So I ask You by Your name which is hidden. O ever-living and
ever-lasting. You are Allah, there is no god but You; You know what is hidden and concealed. I ask You, O Allah, through Your name by
which, when You are asked, You answer and when asked to give,
You do give. I ask You by Your rights on Muhammad and his family
and by their rights on You which You have imposed on Yourself. I
ask that You send Your blessings on Muhammad and his family and
that You fulfill my needs soon. O One who hears supplications, O my
master, O my guardian, O helper. I ask You by every name that You
have named Yourself with, or which You taken for Yourself with the
hidden knowledge that You have send Your blessings on
Muhammad and his family and hasten to remove our difficulties and
fulfill our needs.

After the Dua, go into Sajdah and Supplicate Allah fervently.

(3)Pray two rakat namaz at the place of Ibrahim (a.s.). After the
namaz recite the Tasbeeh of Fatemah Zahra (s.a.) and after
this recite the following Dua

O Allah, by the right of this honorable place; by the rights of those
who worshipped You here. You know my needs, so send Your
blessings on Muhammad and his family and fulfill them. You have
counted my sins so send Your blessings on Muhammad and his
family and forgive my sins. O Allah, grant me life as long as it is good for me and take me away when death is better for me. Make
me befriend Your friends and be an enemy to Your enemies. Deal
with me according to what is most worthy of You, O most merciful of
the merciful ones.

(4)Recite 2 rakats namaz at the corner which is to the west and
towards the Qibla and after that raise up the hands and
recite the following Dua:

O Allah, I have offered these prayers seeking Your pleasures and
beseeching You, hoping for Your support and gifts, so bless
Muhammad and his family and accept the prayers with the best
acceptance. O Allah, by Your mercy, fulfill my hopes and deal with
me according to what is most worthy of You. O most merciful of the merciful ones.

Go into the Sajdah and place each cheek on the ground in turn
and supplicate Allah.

(5) Recite 2 rakat namaz in the eastern corner. After the namaz raise the hands and recite this dua: 

O Allah, my sins and errors have tarnished me in front of You and
have not raised my voice in front of You neither have they led to the
acceptance of my supplications, so I ask You. O Allah, there is no one
like You. I seek intercession through Muhammad and his family and
I ask You to send Your greetings to Muhammad and his family and
to turn to me by Your noble self and to accept my turning to You. Do
not disappoint me when I ask You nor deprive me when I place my
hopes in You, O most merciful of the merciful ones.

(6) After this recite 2 rakats namaz in the other corner in the west side and after the namaz recite the following dua:

O Allah, I ask You by Your name. O Allah, to send Your blessings on
Muhammad and his family and to make the best of my years the last
ones. Make the best of actions to be the last ones and the best of my
days when I meet You, for You are powerful over all things. O Allah,
accept my supplications and hear my invocations, O most High and
great. O one who is most powerful and conquering. O ever-living
who does not die, send Your greetings on Muhammad and his family and forgive those sins that come between me and You. Do not disgrace me in public. Guard me with Your eye that does not
sleep, have mercy on me by Your power over me, O most merciful one. Send Your greetings on our master Muhammad and his pure family, O Lord of the Universe. 

(7) Then recite 2 rakats namaz in the center of the masjid and then recite the following Dua:

O one who is closer to me than my own veins. O one who does what
He wishes, O one who comes between a person and his heart, send
Your greetings on Muhammad and his family and come between us
and what troubles us, by Your power and might. O one who is
sufficient over everything but nothing is complete without Him.
remove our troubles in this and the next world, O most merciful one.""",
