        "arabic":
            """Here we must do the Ziyarat of Hazrat (a.s.) and in the standing position recite:
سَلامُ اللهِ الْكامِلُ التّامُّ الشّامِلُ الْعامُّ، وَصَلَواتُهُ الدّائِمَةُ وَبَرَكاتُهُ الْقائِمَةُ التّامَّةُ عَلى حُجَّةِ اللهِ وَوَلِيِّهِ في اَرْضِهِ وَبِلادِهِ، وَخَليفَتِهِ عَلى خَلْقِهِ وَعِبادِهِ، وَسُلالَةِ النُّبُوَّةِ وَبَقِيَّةِ الْعِتْرَةِ وَالصَّفْوَةِ، صاحِبِ الزَّمانِ وَمُظْهِرِ الاْيمانِ، وَمُلَقِّنِ اَحْكامِ الْقُرْآنِ، وَمُطَهِّرِ الاَرْضِ وَناشِرِ الْعَدْلِ فِي الطُّولِ وَالْعَرْضِ، وَالْحُجِّةِ الْقائِمِ الْمَهْدِيِّ الاِمامِ الْمُنْتَظَرِ الْمَرْضِيِّ، وَابْنِ الاَئِمَّةِ الطّاهِرينَ الْوَصِيِّ ابْنِ الاَوْصِياءِ الْمَرْضِيّينَ الْهادِي الْمَعْصُومِ ابْنِ الاَئِمَّةِ الْهُداةِ الْمَعْصُومينَ، السَّلامُ عَلَيْكَ يا مُعِزَّ الْمُؤْمِنينَ الْمُسْتَضْعَفينَ، السَّلامُ عَلَيْكَ يا مُذِلَّ الْكافِرينَ الْمُتَكَبِّرينَ الظّالِمينَ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكَ يا مَوْلايَ يا صاحِبَ الزَّمانِ، السَّلامُ عَلَيْكَ يَا بْنَ رَسُولِ اللهِ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكَ يَا بْنَ اَميرِ الْمُؤْمِنينَ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكَ يَا بْنَ فاطِمَةَ الزَّهْراءِ سَيِّدَةِ نِساءِ الْعالَمينَ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكَ يَا بْنَ الاَئِمَّةِ الْحُجَجِ الْمَعْصُومينَ وَالاِمامِ عَلَى الْخَلْقِ اَجْمَعينَ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكَ يا مَوْلايَ سَلامَ مُخْلِص لَكَ فِي الْوِلايَةِ، اَشْهَدُ اَنَّكَ الاِمامُ الْمَهْدِىُّ قَوْلاً وَفِعْلاً، وَاَنْتَ الَّذي تَمْلاَُ الاَرْضَ قِسْطاً وَعَدْلاً بَعْدَ ما مُلِئَتْ ظُلْماً وَجَوْراً، فَعَجَّلَ اللهُ فَرَجَكَ وَسَهَّلَ مَخْرَجَكَ وَقَرَّبَ زَمانَكَ وَكَثَّرَ اَنْصارَكَ وَاَعْوانَكَ، وَاَنْجَزَ لَكَ ما وَعَدَكَ فَهُوَ اَصْدَقُ الْقائِلينَ وَنُريدُ اَنْ نَمُنَّ عَلَى الَّذينَ اسْتُضْعِفُوا فِي الاَرْضِ وَنَجْعَلَهُمْ اَئِمَّةً وَنَجْعَلَهُمُ الْوارِثينَ يا مَوْلايَ يا صاحِبَ الزَّمانِ حاجَتي كَذا وَكَذا

mention your needs. Then say:
فَاشْفَعْ لي في نَجاحِها فَقَدْ تَوَجَّهْتُ اِلَيْكَ بِحاجَتي لِعِلْمي اَنَّ لَكَ عِنْدَ اللهِ شَفاعَةً مَقْبُولَةً وَمَقاماً مَحْمُوداً، فَبِحَقِّ مَنِ اخْتَصَّكُمْ بِاَمْرِهِ وَارْتَضاكُمْ لِسِرِّهِ، وَبِالشَّأنِ الَّذي لَكُمْ عِنْدَ اللهِ بَيْنَكُمْ وَبَيْنَهُ، سَلِ اللهَ تَعالى في نُجْحِ طَلِبَتي وَاِجابَةِ دَعْوَتي وَكَشْفِ كُرْبَتي وَ اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكَ يا مَوْلايَ يا صاحِبَ الزَّمانِ وَرَحْمَةُ اللهِ وَبَرَكاتُهُ""",
        "translation":
            """Here we must do the Ziyarat of Hazrat (a.s.) and in the standing position recite:

May the complete, perfect, all-inclusive greetings of Allah and the
ever-lasting, complete blessings be on the proof and special servant
of Allah on His earth and land, His representative to His creatures
and slaves. Greetings on the lineage of Prophecy and remaining
pure family, the master of the time, the one who will proclaim the
laws of the Qur’an. He will purify the earth, spread justice all over
the world, the proof [of Allah] the Qa’im, the rightly guided one, the
expected Imam who Allah is pleased with. He is the contented one,the virtuous, pure, son of the pure Imams. He is the successor, son of
the successors (to the Prophet), the contented ones. He is the guide,
rightly guided, the infallible one, and son of the infallible leaders.
Peace be on you, O inheritor of the knowledge of the Prophets, one
entrusted with the wisdom for the oppressed ones. Peace be on you.
O one who will humiliate the arrogant and oppressive infidels.
Peace be on you, O my master, O master of the time, O son of the
Prophet. Peace be on you, O son of the Commander of the Faithful.
Peace be on you, O son of Fatima al-Zahra, leader of the women of
the Universe. Peace be on you, O son of the Imams, the proofs of
Allah on all creatures. Peace be on you, O my master, greetings of
sincerity in following you. I bear witness that you are the divinely
guided leader by speech and action. You are the one who will fill the
earth with justice and equality just as it will be filled with injustice and oppression. May Allah hasten the end of suffering through you.
May He make your appearance easy and may He hasten the time of
your appearance. May He increase the number of your supporters
and helpers, may He fulfill, through you, what He has promised, for
He is the most honest in speech: “And We wish to bestow favors on
those downtrodden on earth. We wish to make them leaders and
make them inherit tire earth.” O my master, O master of the time,
my needs are such and such …mention your needs. Then say: 

So intercede for me with your Lord so that I may be successful. I
have turned to you with my needs as I know that your intercession
will be accepted by Allah, you have an eminent station with Him. By
the one who has chosen you by His commands and is pleased with
you by confiding His secrets. By the status between you and Him, I
ask Allah to fulfill my needs, answer my prayers and to remove my
difficulties. Peace be on you, O master of the time and may the
mercy and blessings be on you.

Then offer two rak’a salat and recite this dua:

O my Allah, the trials have become great, the matter has become
known and the curtain has been lifted. The earth has become
narrow, and the sky denies (its bounties). You are the one, O my
Lord, to whom complaints are made. You are turned to in difficulty
and ease. O Allah, send Your blessings on Muhammad and the
progeny of Muhammad. You commanded us to obey them and, by that You have made us aware of their status; so remove our
sufferings, by them, with haste, like the twinkle of the eye or faster
than that. O Muhammad, O “Ali, O ‘Ali, O Muhanunad, suffice for me
for both of you are sufficient, help me, for both of you are helpers. O
master of the age, help, help, help, come to me, come to me, come to me.""",
        "transliteration": """""",
      },
      {
        "title": "Masjid of Zaid bin Sawhaan (r.a.)",
        "arabic":
            """There is another Masjid near Sahla Masjid, it is the Masjid of Zaid bin Sawhaan (r.a.). He was a very loyal companion of Hazrat Ali Ibne Abi Talib (a.s.). He was martyred in the Battle of Jamal. Pray 2 rakats namaz here, after that raise your hands and recite the dua:
اِلهي قَدْ مَدَّ اِلَيْكَ الْخاطِىءُ الْمُذْنِبُ يَدَيْهِ بِحُسْنِ ظَنِّهِ بِكَ، اِلهي قَدْ جَلَسَ الُمسيءُ بَيْنَ يَدَيْكَ مُقِرّاً لَكَ بِسُوءِ عَمَلِهِ وَراجِياً مِنْكَ الصَّفْحَ عَنْ زَلَلِهِ، اِلهي قَدْ رَفَعَ اِلَيْكَ الظّالِمُ كَفَّيْهِ راجِياً لِما لَدَيْكَ فَلا تُخَيِّبْهُ بِرَحْمَتِكَ مِنْ فَضْلِكَ، اِلهي قَدْ جَثَا الْعائِدُ اِلى الْمَعاصي بَيْنَ يَدَيْكَ خائِفاً مِنْ يَوْم تَجْثُو فيهِ الْخَلائِقُ بَيْنَ يَدَيْكَ، اِلهي جاءَكَ الْعَبْدُ الْخاطِىءُ فَزِعاً مُشْفِقاً وَرَفَعَ اِلَيْكَ طَرْفَهُ حَذِراً راجِياً، وَفاضَتْ عَبْرَتُهُ مُسْتَغْفِراً نادِماً، وَعِزَّتِكَ وَجَلالِكَ ما اَرَدْتُ بِمَعْصِيَتي مُخالَفَتَكَ، وَما عَصَيْتُكَ اِذْ عَصَيْتُكَ وَاَنَا بِكَ جاهِلٌ، وَلا لِعُقُوبَتِكَ مُتَعَرِّضٌ، وَلا لِنَظَرِكَ مُسْتَخِفٌّ، وَلكِنْ سَوَّلَتْ لي نَفْسي، وَاَعانَتْني عَلى ذلِكَ شَقْوَتي، وَغَرَّني سِتْرُكَ المْرُخْى عَلَيَّ، فَمِنَ الاْنَ مِنْ عَذابِكَ مَنْ يَسْتَنْقِذُني، وَبَحَبْلِ مَنْ اَعْتَصِمُ اِنْ قَطَعْتَ حَبْلَكَ عَنّي، فَيا سَوْاَتاهُ غَداً مِنَ الْوُقُوفِ بَيْنَ يَدَيْكَ اِذا قيلَ لِلْمُخِفّينَ جُوزُوا ولِلْمُثْقِلينَ حُطُّوا، اَفَمَعَ الُْمخِفّينَ اَجُوزُ اَمْ مَعَ الْمُثْقِلينَ اَحُطُّ، وَيْلي كُلَّما كَبُرَ سِنّي كَثُرَتْ ذُنُوبي، وَيْلي كُلَّما طالَ عُمْري كَثُرَتْ مَعاصِيّي، فَكَمْ اَتُوبُ وَكَمْ اَعُودُ اَما آنَ لي اَنْ اَسَتَحْيِيَ مِنْ رَبّي، اَللّـهُمَ فَبِحَِقِّ مُحَمَّد وَآلِ مُحَمَّد اِغْفِرَ لي وَارْحَمَني يا اَرْحَمَ الرّاحِمينَ وَخَيْرَ الْغافِرينَ

Try to weep and place your face on the ground and say:

اِرْحَمْ مَنْ اَساءَ وَاَقْتَرَفَ وَاسْتَكانَ وَاَعْتَرَفَ

Place your right cheek on the ground and say:

اِنْ كُنْتُ بِئْسَ الْعَبْدُ فَاَنْتَ نِعْمَ الرَّبُّ

Place your left cheek on the ground and say:

عَظُمَ الذَّنْبُ مِنْ عَبْدِكَ فَلْيَحْسُنِ الْعَفُْ مِنْ عِنْدِكَ يا كَريمُ

Place your forehead on the Sajdagah (Mohr) and recite 100 times

اَلْعَفْوَ اَلْعَفْوَ""",
        "translation":
            """There is another Masjid near Sahla Masjid, it is the Masjid of Zaid
bin Sawhaan (r.a.). He was a very loyal companion of Hazrat Ali
Ibne Abi Talib (a.s.). He was martyred in the Battle of Jamal.
Pray 2 rakats namaz here, after that raise your hands and recite the dua:

O Allah, the one who errs and the sinner has stretched his hands in
front of You due to His good thoughts of You. The sinner has sat in
front of You professing his evil acts and hoping that You will pardon
his sins. O my Allah, the unjust one has raised his hands to You
hoping that You will give him what is with You so, by Your grace, do
not disappoint him, O Allah. One who returns to sins has come
kneeling to You, scared of the day when all the creatures will come
kneeling in front of You. O Allah, the sinning slave has come to You,
scared and anxious and has raised his eyes to You, cautious and
hopeful, asking for Your forgiveness and is repentant, by Your
might and power. In my disobedience to You I did not wish to
oppose You. When I disobeyed. I was ignorant, neither aware of
Your punishment nor heedless of Your watching me, but my desires
overcame me and the misery helped me in this. The fact that you
hide my defects deceived me. From now on, who will save me from
Your punishment and whose rope shall I cling to if You cut that rope
from me? Shame on me when I will be standing in front of You in the
hereafter. When those with a light burden will be told to pass and
those who have a heavy burden will be asked to stay behind, shall I
be allowed to pass with those of the light burden or stay behind
with those bearing a heavy burden? Woe unto me, every time I grow
older, my sins increase. Woe unto to me, the more my Life was
prolonged, my disobedience increased. So how much shall I repent
and ask for forgiveness? Isn’t it high time for me to be ashamed in
front of my Lord? O Allah, by Muhammad and his family, forgive me
and have mercy on me, O most merciful of the merciful ones and one who is most forgiving.

Try to weep and place your face on the ground and say: 

Have mercy on one who did evil and committed sins and has submitted to You, confessing his sins

Place your right cheek on the ground and say:

If I am the worst servant (of You), then You are the All-excellent Lord.

Place your left cheek on the ground and say:

The sins of Your slave are great so let Your forgiveness be equal to them. O noble one.

Place your forehead on the Sajdagah (Mohr) and recite 100 times 

Forgiveness Forgiveness.""",
        "transliteration": """""",
      },
      {
        "title": "Masjid of Sa’sa bin Sawhaan(r.a.)",
        "arabic":
            """Like his brother Zaid, Sa’sa bin Sawhaan was also a loyal companion of Hazrat Ali (a.s.). He was a powerful orator. He was also present in the funeral of Ali (a.s.). After the burial of Hazrat Ali (a.s.) he stood up, picking up a handful of dust from the grave he put it on his head and delivered a powerful speech. This was the first Majlis that was held at the grave soon after the burial of Ali (a.s.). The preacher was Sa’sa bin Sawhaan and the audience included great personalities like Imam Hasan (a.s.), Imam Husain (a.s.), Hazrat Abbas (a.s.), Janab Mohammad Hanafiya (a.r.). Everyone was weeping. Janab Sa’sa (r.a.) presented condolence to all the sons. After this Majlis, people returned from Najaf to Kufa. We can understand the greatness of Sa’sa from this incident. 

Recite 2 rakats namaz in this Masjid and after that recite the following Dua:

اَللّـهُمَّ يا ذَا الْمِنَنِ السّابِغَةِ، وَالاْلاءِ الْوازِعَةِ، والرَّحْمَةِ الْواسِعَةِ، وَالْقُدْرَةِ الْجامِعَةِ، وَالنِّعَمِ الْجَسْيمَةِ، وَالْمَواهِبِ الْعَظيمَةِ، وَالاَْيادِي الْجَميلَةِ، والْعَطايَا الْجَزيلَةِ، يا مَنْ لا يُنْعَتُ بِتَمْثيل، وَلا يُمَثَّلُ بِنَظير، وَلا يُغْلَبُ بِظَهير، يا مَنْ خَلَقَ فَرَزَقَ وَأَلْهَمَ فَاَنْطَقَ، وَابْتَدَعَ فَشَرَعَ، وَعَلا فَارْتَفَعَ، وَقَدَّرَ فَاَحْسَنَ، وَصَوَّرَ فَاَتْقَنَ، وَاحْتَجَّ فَاَبْلَغَ، وَاَنْعَمَ فَاَسْبَغَ، وَاَعْطى فَاَجْزَلَ، وَمَنَحَ فَاَفْضَلَ، يا مَنْ سَما فِي الْعِزِّ فَفاتَ نَواظِرَ الاْبْصارِ، وَدَنا فِي الُّلطْفِ فَجازَ هَواجِسَ الاَْفْكارِ، يا مَنْ تَوَحَّدَ باِلْمُلكِ فَلا نِدَّ لَهُ في مَلَكُوتِ سُلْطانِهِ، وَتفَرَّدَ بِالاْلاء وَالْكِبرِياءِ فَلا ضِدَّ لَهُ في جَبَرُوتِ شَانِهِ، يا مَنْ حارَتْ في كِبْرِياءِ هَيْبَتِهِ دَقائِقُ لَطائِفِ الاَْوْهامِ، وَانْحَسَرَتْ دُونَ اِدْراكِ عَظَمَتِهِ خَطائِفُ اَبْصارِ الاَْنامِ، يا مَنْ عَنَتِ الْوُجُوهُ لِهَيْبَتِهِ، وَخَضَعَتِ الرِّقابُ لِعَظَمَتِهِ، وَوجِلَتِ الْقُلُوبُ مِنْ خيفَتِهِ، اَساَلُكَ بِهذِهِ الْمِدْحَةِ الَّتي لا تَنْبَغي إِلاّ لَكَ، وَبِما وَأَيْتَ بِهِ عَلى نَفْسِكَ لِداعيكَ مِنَ الْمُؤْمِنينَ، وَبِما ضَمِنْتَ الاِجابَةَ فيهِ عَلى نَفْسِكَ لِلدّاعينَ، يا اَسْمَعَ السّامِعينَ، وَابْصَرَ النّاظِرينَ، وَاَسْرَعَ الْحاسِبينَ، يا ذَا الْقُوَّةِ الْمتينُ، صَلِّ عَلى مُحَمَّد خاتَمِ النَّبِيّينَ، وَعَلى اَهْلِ بَيْتِهِ، وَاقْسِمْ لي في شَهْرِنا هذا خَيْرَ ما قَسَمْتَ، وَاحْتِمْ لي في قَضائِكَ خَيْرَ ما حَتَمْتَ، وَاخْتِمْ لي بِالسَّعادَةِ فيمَنْ خَتَمْتَ، وَاحْيِني ما اَحْيَيْتَني مَوْفُوراً، وَاَمِتْني مَسْرُوراً وَمَغْفُوراً، وَتوَلَّ اَنْتَ نَجاتي مِنْ مُساءَلَةِ الْبَرْزَخِ، وَادْرَأْ عَنّي مُنْكَراً وَنَكيراً، وَاَرِ عَيْني مُبَشِّراً وَبَشيراً، وَاجْعَلْ لي اِلى رِضْوانِكَ وَجِنانِكَ مَصيراً، وَعَيْشاً قَريراً، وَمُلْكاً كَبيْراً، وَصَلِّ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِهِ كَثيراً""",
        "translation":
            """Like his brother Zaid, Sa’sa bin Sawhaan was also a loyal
companion of Hazrat Ali (a.s.). He was a powerful orator. He was
also present in the funeral of Ali (a.s.). After the burial of Hazrat Ali
(a.s.) he stood up, picking up a handful of dust from the grave he
put it on his head and delivered a powerful speech. This was the
first Majlis that was held at the grave soon after the burial of Ali
(a.s.). The preacher was Sa’sa bin Sawhaan and the audience included great personalities like Imam Hasan (a.s.), Imam Husain a.s.), Hazrat Abbas (a.s.), Janab Mohammad Hanafiya (a.r.).
Everyone was weeping. Janab Sa’sa (r.a.) presented condolence to
all the sons. After this Majlis, people returned from Najaf to Kufa.
We can understand the greatness of Sa’sa from this incident.

Recite 2 rakats namaz in this Masjid and after that recite the following Dua:

O Allah, one who has ample favors, abundant blessings, vast mercy
and accumulated power. O one who grants vast blessings, great
gifts and gives in abundance. O one who is not described by
comparison, neither is He described by something equivalent, nor is
He overcome by a helper. O one who creates and sustains, O one
who inspires and makes other speak. O one who creates and
legislates, one who raises and elevates. O one who determines and
perfects, O one who fashions and perfects. O one who argues and proclaims, O one who bestows blessings and makes them abundant.

O one who gives and then increases it, one who grants and bestows.
O one who is elevated by His power so that no-one can imagine Him,
and one, who through His grace, is close yet beyond the thoughts of people; O one who is unique in His kingdom, there is nothing like Him in the kingdom of His sovereignty. He is alone in His bounties
and might. There is no opposition to Him in His mighty status.
Intricate and delicate imaginations are bewildered in awe of His
majesty, the eyes of the people withdraw, dazzled by His grandeur.
O one to whom the faces have submitted due to His grandeur, necks have bowed due to His greatness and the hearts tremble due to His
fear. I ask You by these praises which no one but You deserve and
which You have stored with Yourself for those believers who ask. I ask You by that which You have promised to answer to those who
ask of You. O one who is the best of hearers and seers and one who
is quickest in accounting. O one who is most strong, send Your
blessings on Muhammad, the seal of the Prophets and his pure and
chosen family. Apportion for me in this month the best that You
have apportioned and, in Your decree, make my outcome the best
of all outcomes. Perfect my affairs in the most prosperous manner
and make me live the life of success and make me die in the state of happiness, having been forgiven. Oversee and ensure my salvation,
from the questions posed in Barzakh. Help me from Munkar and
Nakir and show me the bringer of good news. Direct me towards
that which earns me Your pleasure, making my life happy with much
wealth; send Your blessings on Muhammad and his family in the morning and evening.""",
