اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكَ يا اَبا عَبْدِاللهِ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْكَ يا اَبا عَبْدِاللهِ، رَحِمَكَ اللهُ يا اَبا عَبْدِاللهِ، لَعَنَ اللهُ مَنْ قَتَلَكَ، وَلَعَنَ اللهُ مَنْ شَرِكَ فِي دَمِكَ، وَلَعَنَ اللهُ مَنْ بَلَغَهُ ذلِكَ فَرَضِيَ بِهِ اَنَا اِلَى اللهِ مَنْ ذلِكَ بَريءٌ""",
        "translation":
            """It is related from Muawiyah bin Ammar that he asked Imam Sadiq (a.s.): What should I recite when I go for the Ziyarat of Imam Husain (a.s.)? He (a.s.) replied: 

Recite the following

Peace be on you, O Abu Abdullah, may Allah bless you, O Abu Abdullah. May Allah have mercy on you, O Abu Abdullah, May Allah curse the one who killed you and was a partner in spilling your blood and may Allah curse the one who heard about it and remained satisfied with it. I disassociate myself from them in front of Allah""",
