      {
        "title": "Ziyarat of Hazrat Abbas bin Ali (a.s.)",
        "arabic":
            """The respected scholar Jafar bin Qulwayh (r.a.) has related through reliable chains from Abu Hamza Sumali (r.a.) that Hazrat Imam Jafar Sadiq (a.s.) said:
When you decide to perform the Ziyarat of the grave of Abbas bin Ali, which is on the banks of Furaat and opposite the holy precincts, stand at the gate of the tomb and recite:

سَلامُ اللهِ وَسَلامُ مَلائِكَتِهِ الْمُقَرَّبينَ وَاَنْبِيائِهِ الْمُرْسَلينَ وَعِبادِهِ الصّالِحينَ وَجَميعِ الشُّهَداءِ وَالصِّدّيقينَ، وَالزَّاكِياتُ الطَّيِّباتُ فيـما تَغْتَدي وَتَرُوحُ عَلَيْكَ يَا بْنَ اَميرِ الْمُؤْمِنينَ، اَشْهَدُ لَكَ بِالتَّسْليمِ وَالتَّصْديقِ وَالْوَفاءِ وَالنَّصيحَةِ لِخَلَفِ النَّبِيِّ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَآلِهِ الْمُرْسَلِ، وَالسِّبْطِ الْمُنْتَجَبِ، وَالدَّليلِ الْعالِمِ، وَالْوَصِيِّ الْمُبَلِّغِ، وَالْمَظْلُومِ الْمُهْتَضَمِ، فَجَزاكَ اللهُ عَنْ رَسُولِهِ وَعَنْ اَميرِ الْمُؤْمِنينَ وَعَنِ الْحَسَنِ وَالْحُسَيْنِ صَلَواتُ اللهِ عَلَيْهِمْ اَفْضَلَ الْجَزاءِ بِما صَبَرْتَ وَاحْتَسَبْتَ وَاَعَنْتَ فَنِعْمَ عُقْبَى الدّارِ، لَعَنَ اللهُ مَنْ قَتَلَكَ وَلَعَنَ اللهُ مَنْ جَهِلَ حَقَّكَ وَاسْتَخَفَّ بِحُرْمَتِكَ، وَلَعَنَ اللهُ مَنْ حالَ بَيْنَكَ وَبَيْنَ ماءِ الْفُراتِ، اَشْهَدُ اَنَّكَ قُتِلْتَ مَظْلُوماً، وَاَنَّ اللهَ مُنْجِزٌ لَكُمْ ما وَعَدَكُمْ، جِئْتُكَ يَا بْنَ اَميرِ اْلُمْؤْمِنينَ وَافِداً اِلَيْكُمْ، وَقَلْبي مُسَلِّمٌ لَكُمْ وَتابِعٌ، وَاَنَا لَكُمْ تابِـعٌ وَنُصْرَتي لَكُمْ مُعَدَّةٌ حَتّى يَحْكُمَ اللهُ وَهُوَ خَيْرُ الْحاكِمينَ، فَمَعَكُمْ مَعَكُمْ لا مَعَ عَدُوِّكُمْ اِنّي بِكُمْ وَبِإيابِكُمْ مِنَ الْمُؤْمِنينَ، وَبِمَنْ خالَفَكُمْ وَقَتَلَكُمْ مِنَ الْكافَرينَ، قَتَلَ اللهُ اُمَّةً قَتَلَتْكُمْ بِالاَْيْدي وَ الاَْلْسُنِ

Then enter the shrine and clinging to the Zari say:

اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكَ اَيُّهَا الْعَبْدُ الصّالِحُ الْمُطيعُ للهِ وَلِرَسُولِهِ وَلاَِميرِالْمُؤْمِنينَ وَالْحَسَنِ والْحُسَيْنِ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِمْ وَسَلَّمَ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكَ وَرَحْمَةُ اللهِ وَبَرَكاتُهُ وَمَغْفِرَتُهُ وَرِضْوانُهُ وَعَلى رُوحِكَ وَبَدَنِكَ، اَشْهَدُ و اُشْهِدُ اللهَ اَنَّكَ مَضَيْتَ عَلى ما مَضى بِهِ الْبَدْرِيُّونَ وَالُْمجاهِدُونَ فِي سَبيلِ اللهِ الْمُناصِحُونَ لَهُ فِي جِهادِ اَعْدائِهِ الْمُبالِغُونَ فِي نُصْرَةِ اَوْلِيائِهِ الذّابُّونَ عَنْ اَحِبّائِهِ فَجَزاكَ اللهُ اَفْضَلَ الْجَزاءِ، وَاَكْثَرَ الْجَزاءِ، وَاَوْفَرَ الْجَزاءِ، وَاَوْفى جَزاءِ اَحَد مِمَّنْ وَفى بِبَيْعَتِهِ وَاسْتَجابَ لَهُ دَعْوَتَهُ وَاَطاعَ وُلاةَ، اَمْرِهِ اَشْهَدُ اَنَّكَ قَدْ بالَغْتَ فِي النَّصيحَةِ، وَاَعْطَيْتَ غايَةَ اْلَْمجْهُودِ، فَبَعَثَكَ اللهُ فِي الشُّهَداءِ، وَجَعَلَ رُوحَكَ مَعَ اَرْواحِ السُّعَداءِ، وَاَعْطاكَ مِنْ جِنانِهِ اَفْسَحَها مَنْزِلاً وَاَفْضَلَها غُرَفاً، وَرَفَعَ ذِكْرَكَ فِي عِلِّيّينَ، وَحَشَرَكَ مَعَ النَّبِيّينَ وَالصِّدّيقينَ وَالشُّهَداءِ وَالصّالِحينَ وَحَسُنَ اُولئِكَ رَفيقاً، اَشْهَدُ اَنَّكَ لَمْ تَهِنْ وَلَمْ تَنْكُلْ، وَاَنَّكَ مَضَيْتَ عَلى بَصيرَة مِنْ اَمْرِكَ مُقْتَدِياً بِالصّالِحينَ، وَمُتَّبِعاً لِلنَّبِيّينَ، فَجَمَعَ اللهُ بَيْنَنا وَبَيْنَكَ وَبَيْنَ رَسُولِهِ وَاَوْلِيائِهِ فِي مَنازِلِ الُْمخْبِتينَ، فَاِنَّهُ اَرْحَمُ الرّاحِمينَ

The writer says: It is better if this Ziyarat is recited at the back of the grave in the direction of qibla as mentioned by Shaykh (r.a.) inTahzeeb.
We should know that according to traditions the Ziyarat of Hazrat Abbas (a.s) is the same that we have already mentioned. But Sayyid Ibne Taaoos (a.r.), Shaykh Mufeed (a.r.) have said after this: Then go to the head side and recite 2 rakats namaz and after that recite whichever namaz you want and supplicate Allah. After the namaz recite the following dua:

اَللّـهُمَّ صَلِّ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِ مُحَمَّد، وَلا تَدَعْ لي فِي هذَا الْمَكانِ الْمُكَرَّمِ وَالْمَشْهَدِ الْمُعَظَّمِ ذَنْباً اِلاّ غَفَرْتَهُ، وَلا هَمّاً اِلاّ فَرَّجَتَهُ، وَلا مَرَضاً اِلاّ شَفَيْتَهُ، وَلا عَيْباً اِلاّ سَتَرْتَهُ، وَلا رِزْقاً اِلاّ بَسَطْتَهُ، وَلا خَوْفاً الاّ آمَنْتَهُ، وَلا شَمْلاً اِلاّ جَمَعْتَهُ، وَلا غائِباً اِلاّ حَفَظْتَهُ وَاَدْنَيْتَهُ، وَلا حاجَةً مِنْ حَوائِجِ الدُّنْيا وَالاْخِرَةِ لَكَ فيها رِضىً وَلِيَ فيها صَلاحٌ اِلاّ قَضَيْتَها يا اَرْحَمَ الرّاحِمينَ

Then turn towards the Zari and standing at the footside recite:

اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكَ يا اَبَا الْفَضْلِ الْعَبّاسَ ابْنَ اَميرِ الْمُؤْمِنينَ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكَ يَا بْنَ سَيِّدِ الْوَصِيّينَ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكَ يَا بْنَ اَوَّلِ الْقَوْمِ اِسْلاماً وَاَقْدَمِهِمْ ايماناً وَاَقْوَمِهِمْ بِدينِ اللهِ، وَاَحْوَطِهِمْ عَلَى الاِْسْلامِ، اَشْهَدُ لَقَدْ نَصَحْتَ للهِ وَلِرَسُولِهِ وَلاَِخيكَ فَنِعْمَ الاَْخُ الْمُواسي، فَلَعَنَ اللهُ اُمَّةً قَتَلَتْكَ، وَلَعَنَ اللهُ اُمَّةً ظَلَمَتْكَ، وَلَعَنَ اللهُ اُمَّةً اسْتَحَلَّتْ مِنْكَ الَْمحارِمَ، وَانْتَهَكَتْ حُرْمَةَ الاِْسْلامِ، فَنِعْمَ الصّابِرُ الُْمجاهِدُ الُْمحامِي النّاصِرُ وَالاَْخُ الدّافِعُ عَنْ اَخيهِ، الُْمجيبُ اِلى طاعَةِ رَبِّهِ، الرّاغِبُ فيـما زَهِدَ فيهِ غَيْرُهُ مِنَ الثَّوابِ الْجَزيلِ وَالثَّناءِ الْجَميلِ، وَاَلْحَقَكَ اللهُ بِدَرَجَةِ آبائِكَ فِي جَنّاتِ النَّعيمِ، اَللّـهُمَّ اِنّي تَعَرَّضْتُ لِزِيارَةِ اَوْلِيائِكَ رَغْبَةً فِي ثَوابِكَ وَرَجاءً لِمَغْفِرَتِكَ وَجَزيلِ اِحْسانِكَ، فَاَسْاَلُكَ اَنْ تُصَلِّيَ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِهِ الطّاهِرينَ، وَاَنْ تَجْعَلَ رِزْقي بِهِمْ دارّاً وَعَيْشي بِهِمْ قارّاً، وَزِيارَتي بِهِمْ مَقْبُولَةً وَحَياتي بِهِمْ طَيِّبَةً، وَاَدْرِجْني اِدْراجَ الْمُكْرَمينَ، وَاجْعَلْني مِمَّنْ يَنْقَلِبُ مِنْ زِيارَةِ مَشاهِدِ اَحِبّائِكَ مُفْلِحاً مُنْجِحاً، قَدِ اسْتَوْجَبَ غُفْرانَ الذُّنُوبِ وَسَتْرَ الْعُيُوبِ وَكَشْفَ الْكُرُوبِ، اِنَّكَ اَهْلُ التَّقْوى وَاَهْلُ الْمَغْفِرَةِ 

And when you wish to bid farewell you should go near the grave and recite this, which is in the tradition of Abu Hamza Sumali (r.a.) and other scholars have also mentioned it:

اَسْتَوْدِعُكَ اللهَ وَاَسْتَرْعيكَ وَاَقْرَأُ عَلَيْكَ اَلسَّلامَ، آمَنّا بِاللهِ وَبِرَسُولِهِ وَبِكِتابِهِ وَبِما جاءَ بِهِ مِنْ عِنْدِ اللهِ، اَللّـهُمَّ فَاكْتُبْنا مَعَ الشّاهِدينَ، اَللّـهُمَّ لا تَجْعَلْهُ آخِرَ الْعَهْدِ مِنْ زِيارَتي قَبْرَ ابْنِ اَخي رَسُولِكَ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَآلِهِ، وَارْزُقْني زِيارَتَهُ اَبَداً ما اَبْقَيْتَني وَاحْشُرْني مَعَهُ وَمَعَ آبائِهِ فِي الجِنانِ، وَعَرِّفْ بَيْني وَبَيْنَهُ وَبَيْنَ رَسُولِكَ وَاَوْلِيائِكَ، اَللّـهُمَّ صَلِّ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِ مُحَمَّد وَتَوَفَّني عَلَى الاْيمانِ بِكَ وَالتَّصْديقِ بِرَسُولِكَ وَالْوِلايَةِ لِعَليِّ بْنِ اَبي طالِب وَالاَْئِمَّةِ مِنْ وُلْدِهِ عَلَيْهِمُ السَّلامُ وَالْبَراءَةِ مِنْ عَدُوِّهِمْ، فَاِنّي قَدْ رَضيتُ يا رَبِّي بِذلِكَ، وَصَلَّى اللهُ عَلى مُحَمَّد وَآلِ مُحَمَّد

After this pray for yourself, your parents, believers and Muslims and ask for whatever you desire. The writer says: A tradition is related from Hazrat Imam Zainul Aabedeen (a.s.) which in brief is that he (a.s.) said:
May Allah have mercy on Abbas that he gave sacrifice for his brother and gave away his life for him but continued to help Imam Husain (a.s.). The enemies severed both hishands in lieu of which Allah bestowed him two wings. With these wings he flies in Paradise with the Angels like Jafar at-Tayyaar. Abbas is having such a status before Allah that on the day of Qiyamat martyrs would envy it and they would vie for his position.""",
        "translation":
            """The respected scholar Jafar bin Qulwayh (r.a.) has related through
reliable chains from Abu Hamza Sumali (r.a.) that Hazrat Imam Jafar Sadiq (a.s.) said:

When you decide to perform the Ziyarat of the grave of Abbas bin Ali, which is on the banks of Furaat and
opposite the holy precincts, stand at the gate of the tomb and recite: 

May the greetings of Allah, His close angels and the Prophets sent by Allah be on you. May the greetings of His pious servants, all martyrs and truthful ones, who are virtuous and pure, who frequent
you, be on you. O son of the Commander of the Faithful. I bear witness that you submitted yourself to the will of Allah; you were
faithful, giving sound advice to the descendant of the Prophet(s.a.w.a.) and to his chosen grandson. He (Husayn) is the universal
guide, the successor who proclaimed. He was oppressed. On behalf of His Messenger, the Commander of the Faithful, al-Hasan and alHusayn (a.s.) may Allah grant you the best reward due to your patience, support and help. How excellent is the reward in the eternal life. May Allah curse those who killed you, ignored your
rights and gave no importance to your sanctity. May the curse of Allah be on those who stood between you and the river Furat. I bear witness that you were oppressed when killed and that Allah will reward you with what He has promised. 

I have come to you, O son of the Commander of the Faithful, to present myself before you. My heart has submitted to you and follows you. I am your disciple. I am ready to serve you until Allah judges, for He is the best judge. I am
with you, with you, not with your enemies. I believe in you and in your return with other believers. I believe in the return of those infidels who opposed and killed you. May Allah destroy those who killed you by their hands and tongues. 

Then enter the shrine and clinging to the Zari say:

Peace be on you, O pious, obedient servant of Allah and on His
messenger, and on the Commander of the Faithful, on al-Hasan and
al-Husayn (a.s.). May the blessings and greetings of Allah be on
them. Peace be on you and may the mercy and blessings,
forgiveness and pleasure of Allah be on you and on your body and
soul. I bear witness and invoke Allah to be a witness that verily you
trod the path of the warriors of Badr and those striving in the cause
of Allah. You served Him faithfully in the battlefield against His
enemies. You were like those who exerted themselves to support
His friends and defend His beloved favourites. May Allah grant you
the best, vast, continuous, exemplary and conclusive reward that He
gives to those who are loyal to their allegiances, who answer His call
and obey those who exercise authority on His behalf. I bear witness
that you exerted yourself in giving sound advice, and made utmost
efforts to pursue its purpose. May Allah raise you with the martyrs
and let your soul be with the prosperous ones. He has awarded you
a special place and chamber in His Paradise. He has made mention of your name in the illiyin, the highest circle in heaven. He gathered you with the Prophets, the truthful ones, the martyrs and the pious,they are the best companions. I bear witness that you were not
feeble nor did you turn away. You had insight into your matters following in the footsteps of the pious and the Prophets, so may Allah assemble us with His Prophets and His friends in the station of those who are humble, for verily He is the most merciful one.  

The writer says: It is better if this Ziyarat is recited at the back of the
grave in the direction of qibla as mentioned by Shaykh (r.a.) in Tahzeeb. 

We should know that according to traditions the Ziyarat of Hazrat Abbas (a.s) is the same that we have already mentioned. But Sayyid Ibne Taaoos (a.r.), Shaykh Mufeed (a.r.) have said after this:
Then go to the head side and recite 2 rakats namaz and after that recite whichever namaz you want and supplicate Allah. After the namaz recite the following dua: 


O Allah, send Your blessings on Muhammad and his family. At this honorable and elevated sanctuary, do not leave any sin of mine unforgiven, nor any difficulties without removing them. Cure every sickness, hide all defects. Spread Your sustenance, do not leave any fear except that You have removed it, nor any group except that You have united it. Do not leave any hidden thing unprotected, fulfill my desires in this and the next world that You are happy with and which are in my interest, O most merciful one.

Then turn towards the Zari and standing at the footside recite: 

Peace be on you, O Abul Fazl al-’Abbas, son of the Commander of
the Faithful. Peace be on you, O son of the leaders of the successor.
Peace be on you, O son of the first in the community to submit and
the foremost in faith. He was the strongest in the religion of Allah
and the best guard of Islam. I bear witness that you admonished the
people for the sake of Allah, His Messenger and your brother. How
nice is the brother who is sympathetic. May Allah curse those who
killed you. May Allah curse those who oppressed you. May Allah
curse those who treated the unlawful as lawful and violated the
sanctity of Islam. How great is the brother who is forbearing, wages
war against the unbelievers, protects and helps. He is one who
defends his brother, obedient to the commandment of his Lord,
desiring to refrain from what others keep away so as to attain
abundant reward and great praises. 

May Allah honor you with the status of your fore fathers in the blessed abode. O Allah, I have desired to visit Your friends, seeking Your rewards and hoping for
forgiveness and abundant goodness from You. I ask You to send blessings on Muhammad and his pure household. Due to them, fix
my sustenance and make my life stable. Due to them, accept my ziyarat and make my life pure. Make me amongst the noble ones
and amongst those who return from visiting the holy sites of Your friends, successful and saved. Make me amongst those who deserve
their sins to be forgiven, defects concealed and difficulties removed. Verily, from You comes piety and forgiveness. 

And when you wish to bid farewell you should go near the grave and recite this, which is in the tradition of Abu Hamza Sumali (r.a.) and other scholars have also mentioned it: 

I bid farewell to you and I sent my greetings to you, believing in Allah, His Prophet, the book and in what has come from Allah. O Allah, record us amongst those who have witnessed, do not make this my last visitation to the grave of the son of the brother of Your Prophet, peace be on him and his family. Grant me a chance to visit him for as long as I am alive. Gather me with him and his ancestors in the gardens. Bring me closer to him and Your Prophet and friends. O Allah, send Your blessings on Muhammad and his family,make me die believing in You and Your Prophet, following Ali b. Abi Talib and the Imams amongst his children (a.s.), dissociating from their enemies for I am happy with that. O my Lord, send Your greetings on Muhammad and his family

After this pray for yourself, your parents, believers and Muslims and ask for whatever you desire. The writer says: A tradition is related from Hazrat Imam Zainul Aabedeen (a.s.) which in brief is that he (a.s.) said: 

May Allah have mercy on Abbas that he gave sacrifice for his brother and gave away his life for him but continued to help Imam Husain (a.s.). The enemies severed both his hands in lieu of which Allah bestowed him two wings.

With these wings he flies in Paradise with the Angels like Jafar at-Tayyaar. Abbas is having such a status before Allah that on the day of Qiyamat martyrs would envy it and they would vie for his position.""",
