      {
        "title": "Common Ziyarat of Imam Kazim(a.s) and Imam Taqi(a.s)",
        "arabic":
            """This is the common Ziyarat for both Imams, Imam Musa Kazim (a.s.) and Imam Mohammad Taqi (a.s.). Stand near the Zari and recite as follows:

اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكُما يا وَلِيَّيِ اللهِ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكُما يا حُجَّتَيِ اللهِ، اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكُما يا نُورَيِ اللهِ في ظُلُماتِ الاَْرْضِ، اَشْهَدُ اَنَّكُما قَدْ بَلَّغْتُما عَنِ اللهِ ما حَمَّلَكُما، وَحَفِظْتُما مَا اسْتَودَعْتُما، وَحَلَّلْتُما حَلالَ اللهِ وَحَرَّمْتُما حَرامَ اللهِ، وَاَقَمْتُما حُدُودَ اللهِ، وَتَلَوْتُما كِتابَ اللهِ، وَصَبَرْتُما عَلَى الاَْذى في جَنْبِ اللهِ مُحْتَسبَيْنَ حَتّى اَتاكُمَا الْيَقينُ، اَبْرَأُ اِلَى اللهِ مِنْ اَعْدائِكُما، وَاَتَقَرَّبُ اِلَى اللهِ بِوِلايَتِكُما، اَتَيْتُكُما زائِراً عارِفاً بِحَقِّكُما، مُوالِياً لاَِوْلِيائِكُما، مُعادِياً لاَِعْدائِكُما مُسْتَبْصِراً بِالْهُدَى الَّذي اَنْتُما عَلَيْهِ، عارِفاً بِضَلالَةِ مَنْ خالَفَكُما، فَاشْفَعا لي عِنْدَ رَبِّكُما فَاِنَّ لَكُما عِنْدَ اللهِ جاهاً عَظيماً وَمَقاماً مَحْمُوداً

After the Ziyarat kiss the shrine and go to the headside and recite as follows:

اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكُما يا حُجَّتَيِ اللهِ في اَرْضِهِ وَسَمائِهِ، عَبْدُكُما وَوَلِيُّكُما زائِرُكُما مُتَقَرِّباً اِلَى اللهِ بِزِيارَتِكُما، اَللّـهُمَّ اجْعَلْ لي لِسانَ صِدْق في اَوْلِيائِكَ الْمُصْطَفَيْنَ، وَحَبِّبْ اِلَيَّ مَشاهِدَهُمْ وَاجْعَلْني مَعَهُمْ في الدُّنْيا وَالاْخِرَةِ يا اَرْحَمَ الرّاحِمينَ

Two rakats namaz will be performed with the intention of the Ziyarat of Imam Musa Kazim (a.s.) and two rakats for the Ziyarat of Imam Mohammad Taqi (a.s.).""",
        "translation":
            """This is the common Ziyarat for both Imams, Imam Musa Kazim(a.s.) and Imam Mohammad Taqi (a.s.). Stand near the Zari and recite as follows: 

Peace be on both of you, O the representatives of Allah! Peace be on both of you, O the decisive arguments of Allah! Peace be on both of you, O the lights of Allah in the darkness of the (ignorant) world! I bear witness that, verily, you had successfully carried and delivered that for which Allah had commissioned you, protected that which was entrusted to you, prescribed that which Allah has made lawful,proscribed that which Allah has made unlawful, made clear the divine rules, studied and interpreted the Book of Allah, while directing affairs in the light of the divine rules, exercised selfcontrol bravely in the midst of offensive provocations, till the inevitable came unto you I turn to Allah by disconnecting all links with your enemies, I seek nearness to Allah through my love for you,

I have come near you, fully aware of your rights, attached to your friends, averse to your enemies, well acquainted with the guidance you adhered to, mindful of the depravity of your opponents, so,speak on my behalf before your Lord, because, verily, your grandeur, before Allah, is the most exalted, your position is highly celebrated. 

After the Ziyarat kiss the shrine and go to the headside and recite as follows: 

Peace be on both of you, O the decisive proofs of Allah on His earth and in His heavens. Your servant, your friend, has come to visit you,in order to seek Allah's nearness through your "Ziyaarat" O Allah make me speak the truth about Your chosen friends, render my visit to them winsome, and let me be with them in this world and in the Hereafter, O the Most Merciful!

Two rakats namaz will be performed with the intention of the Ziyarat of Imam Musa Kazim (a.s.) and two rakats for the Ziyarat of Imam Mohammad Taqi (a.s.).""",
        "transliteration": """""",
      },
      {
        "title": "Farewell to Imam Musa Kazim (a.s.)",
        "arabic":
            """When you intend to leave the town of these two Imams (a.s.) and you want to bid them farewell, you should recite Duas regarding
farewell. One of them is the one quoted by Shaykh Tusi (a.r.) in Tahzeeb and then he says: When you want to bid farewell to Imam Musa Kazim (a.s.) you should stand near the grave and say:

اَلسَّلامُ عَلَيْكَ يا مَوْلايَ يا اَبَا الْحَسَنِ وَرَحْمَةُ اللهِ وَبَرَكاتُهُ، اَسْتَوْدِعُكَ اللهَ وَاَقْرَأُ، عَلَيْكَ السَّلامَ آمَنّا بِاللهِ وَبِالرَّسُولِ وَبِما جِئْتَ بِهِ وَدَلَلْتَ عَلَيْهِ، اَللّـهُمَّ اَكْتُبْنا مَعَ الشّاهِدينَ""",
        "translation":
            """When you intend to leave the town of these two Imams (a.s.) and
you want to bid them farewell, you should recite Duas regarding farewell. One of them is the one quoted by Shaykh Tusi (a.r.) in Tahzeeb and then he says: When you want to bid farewell to Imam Musa Kazim (a.s.) you should stand near the grave and say:

Peace be on you, O my master, O Abul Hasan and the mercy of Allah and His Blessings. I entrust you to Allah and I send salutations to you. We believe in Allah and His Apostle and in what you have brought and indicated towards. O Allah! Do write us among the witnesses.""",
