        "arabic":
            """That is Janab Abu Amr Usmaan bin Saeed Amri, Janab Abu Jafar Mohammad bin Usmaan, Shaykh Abul Qasim Husain bin Rawh Nawbakhti and the great Shaykh Abul Hasan Ali Ibne Mohammad Saymoori (May Allah be pleased with them all). During their stay at Kazmayn, one of the duties of the pilgrims is that they should go to Baghdad for the Ziyarat of the four special deputies of Imam Zamana (a.t.f.s.). Even if each of them had been buried at far off places it still would have been necessary to bear the difficulties of travel and visit them, because none of the special companions of the Imams could reach upto their level. For approximately 70 years they were medium between Imam Zaman (a.t.f.s.) and his followers. Many miracles also became apparent due to their existence. It is said that some scholars considered them infallible. But it is clear that they were conduit between Imam Zamaan (a.t.f.s.) and his followers and their duties included the conveying of their requests, letters and questions to the Imam (a.s.). Even now they are upon this post. In their difficult times they convey their requests only through these personalities. In brief, their merits are beyond description. This much is sufficient to make the pilgrims attracted towards their Ziyarat. The method of their Ziyarat is mentioned by Shaykh (r.a.) in Tahzeeb and by Sayyid Ibne Taaoos (r.a.) in Misbaahuz Zaaereen. He has related it from Husain Ibne Rauh Nawbakhti (r.a.) that he said regarding his Ziyarat: First send your salutations on the Prophet (s.a.w.a.), then Ameerul Momeneen (a.s.) and Khadijatul Kubraa (s.a.), then Fatemah Zahra (s.a.), Hasan (a.s.), Husain (a.s.) till the 12th Imam and then recite:
السَّلاَمُ عَلَيْكَ يَا فُلاَنَ بْنَ فُلاَنٍ‏

In place of 
فُلاَنَ بْنَ فُلاَنٍ 

mention the name of the buried person and the name of his father then say:
أَشْهَدُ أَنَّكَ بَابُ الْمَوْلَى أَدَّيْتَ عَنْهُ وَ أَدَّيْتَ إِلَيْهِ مَا خَالَفْتَهُ وَ لاَ خَالَفْتَ عَلَيْهِ قُمْتَ خَاصّاً وَ انْصَرَفْتَ سَابِقاً
جِئْتُكَ عَارِفاً بِالْحَقِّ الَّذِي أَنْتَ عَلَيْهِ وَ أَنَّكَ مَا خُنْتَ فِي التَّأْدِيَةِ وَ السَّفَارَةِ
السَّلاَمُ عَلَيْكَ مِنْ بَابٍ مَا أَوْسَعَهُ وَ مِنْ سَفِيرٍ مَا آمَنَكَ وَ مِنْ ثِقَةٍ مَا أَمْكَنَكَ‏
أَشْهَدُ أَنَّ اللَّهَ اخْتَصَّكَ بِنُورِهِ حَتَّى عَايَنْتَ الشَّخْصَ فَأَدَّيْتَ عَنْهُ وَ أَدَّيْتَ إِلَيْهِ 

Then come back and recite salutations from the Holy Prophet (s.a.w.a.) till Imam Zamana (a.s.), upon all the Imams, and say:
جِئْتُكَ مُخْلِصاً بِتَوْحِيدِ اللَّهِ وَ مُوَالاَةِ أَوْلِيَائِهِ وَ الْبَرَاءَةِ مِنْ أَعْدَائِهِمْ 
وَ مِنَ الَّذِينَ خَالَفُوكَ يَا حُجَّةَ الْمَوْلَى وَ بِكَ إِلَيْهِمْ تَوَجُّهِي وَ بِهِمْ إِلَى اللَّهِ تَوَسُّلِي 

After this ask for whatever you want, it will be accepted Insha Allah.

The writer says: One should also perform the Ziyarat of Shaykh Kulaini (r.a.) in Baghdad as he was the greatest hadees scholar of shias and he had compiled the magnum opus Al-Kafi after 20 years of back breaking labour. Actually he has done a great favour on the Shias and on Shia scholars. Regarding his status Ibne Aseer has written: He was a 3rd century Shia scholar and traditionist.""",
        "translation":
            """That is Janab Abu Amr Usmaan bin Saeed Amri, Janab Abu Jafar
Mohammad bin Usmaan, Shaykh Abul Qasim Husain bin Rawh
Nawbakhti and the great Shaykh Abul Hasan Ali Ibne Mohammad
Saymoori (May Allah be pleased with them all). During their stay at
Kazmayn, one of the duties of the pilgrims is that they should go
to Baghdad for the Ziyarat of the four special deputies of Imam
Zamana (a.t.f.s.). Even if each of them had been buried at far off
places it still would have been necessary to bear the difficulties of
travel and visit them, because none of the special companions of
the Imams could reach upto their level. 


For approximately 70 years they were medium between Imam Zaman (a.t.f.s.) and his followers. Many miracles also became apparent due to their existence. It is said that some scholars considered them infallible.

But it is clear that they were conduit between Imam Zamaan(a.t.f.s.) and his followers and their duties included the conveying of their requests, letters and questions to the Imam (a.s.). Even now they are upon this post. In their difficult times they convey their requests only through these personalities. In brief, their merits are beyond description. This much is sufficient to make the pilgrims attracted towards their Ziyarat. The method of their Ziyarat is mentioned by Shaykh (r.a.) in Tahzeeb and by Sayyid Ibne Taaoos (r.a.) in Misbaahuz Zaaereen. He has related it from Husain Ibne Rauh Nawbakhti (r.a.) that he said regarding his Ziyarat: First send your salutations on the Prophet (s.a.w.a.), then Ameerul Momeneen (a.s.) and Khadijatul Kubraa (s.a.), then Fatemah Zahra (s.a.), Hasan (a.s.), Husain (a.s.) till the 12th Imam and then recite

ASSALAAMO ALAYKA(WHOEVER NAME YOU HAVE TO TAKE)-> mention the name of the buried person and the name of his father then say:

I attest that you are the door to the master, you have conveyed messages from him and also to him neither did you oppose him nor did nor did you have any difference of opinion concerning him You established yourself on the special deputyship and were the foremost in devotion to him.I come to you, cognizant of the rights which you enjoy and you did not perform any breach in matters of conveyance of message and deputyship. Peace be on you, O what an expansive door you were and what a trustworthy deputy you were and you were having a very lofty position of trust and reliability. 

I bear witness that Allah has particularized you by His Might so much so that you had the honour of seeing Imam (a.s.) and conveying to and for the messages concerning and from him.

Then come back and recite salutations from the Holy Prophet(s.a.w.a.) till Imam Zamana (a.s.), upon all the Imams, and say: 

I come to you, sincere in the unity of unity and with the love and friendship of His friends and disawoval of their enemies and of those who had opposed you. O the proof of the master! I have turned to them through you and I beseech Allah through them.

After this ask for whatever you want, it will be accepted InshaAllah.

The writer says: One should also perform the Ziyarat of Shaykh Kulaini (r.a.) in Baghdad as he was the greatest hadees scholar of shias and he had compiled the magnum opus Al-Kafi after 20 years of back breaking labour. Actually he has done a great favour on the Shias and on Shia scholars. Regarding his status Ibne Aseer has written: He was a 3rd century Shia scholar and traditionist.""",
